INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 1, 'In the thirtieth year, in the fourth [month], on the fifth [day] of the month, while I was among the exiles by the Chebar Canal, the heavens opened and I saw visions of God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 2, 'On the fifth [day] of the month-- it was the fifth year of King Jehoiachin''s exile--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 3, 'the word of the LORD came directly to Ezekiel the priest, the son of Buzi, in the land of the Chaldeans by the Chebar Canal. And the LORD''s hand was on him there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 4, 'I looked and there was a whirlwind coming from the north, a great cloud with fire flashing back and forth and brilliant light all around it. In the center of the fire, there was a gleam like amber.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 5, 'The form of four living creatures came from it. And this was their appearance: They had human form,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 6, 'but each of them had four faces and four wings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 7, 'Their legs were straight, and the soles of their feet were like the hooves of a calf, sparkling like the gleam of polished bronze.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 8, '[They had] human hands under their wings on their four sides. All four of them had faces and wings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 9, 'Their wings were touching. The creatures did not turn as they moved; each one went straight ahead.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 10, 'The form of [each of] their faces was that of a man, and each of the four had the face of a lion on the right, the face of an ox on the left, and the face of an eagle.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 11, '[That is what] their faces [were like]. Their wings were spread upward; each had two [wings] touching that of another and two wings covering its body.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 12, 'Each creature went straight ahead. Wherever the Spirit wanted to go, they went without turning as they moved.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 13, 'The form of the living creatures was like the appearance of burning coals of fire and torches. Fire was moving back and forth between the living creatures; it was bright, with lightning coming out of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 14, 'The creatures were darting back and forth like flashes of lightning.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 15, 'When I looked at the living creatures, there was one wheel on the ground beside each creature that had four faces.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 16, 'The appearance of the wheels and their craftsmanship was like the gleam of beryl, and all four had the same form. Their appearance and craftsmanship was like a wheel within a wheel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 17, 'When they moved, they went in any of the four directions, without pivoting as they moved.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 18, 'Their rims were large and frightening. Each of their four rims were full of eyes all around.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 19, 'So when the living creatures moved, the wheels moved beside them, and when the creatures rose from the earth, the wheels also rose.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 20, 'Wherever the Spirit wanted to go, the creatures went in the direction the Spirit was moving. The wheels rose alongside them, for the spirit of the living creatures was in the wheels.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 21, 'When the creatures moved, the wheels moved; when the creatures stood still, the wheels stood still; and when the creatures rose from the earth, the wheels rose alongside them, for the spirit of the living creatures was in the wheels.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 22, 'The shape of an expanse, with a gleam like awe-inspiring crystal, was spread out over the heads of the living creatures.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 23, 'And under the expanse their wings extended one toward another. Each of them also had two wings covering their bodies.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 24, 'When they moved, I heard the sound of their wings like the roar of mighty waters, like the voice of the Almighty, and a sound of commotion like the noise of an army. When they stood still, they lowered their wings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 25, 'A voice came from above the expanse over their heads; when they stood still, they lowered their wings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 26, 'The shape of a throne with the appearance of sapphire stone was above the expanse. There was a form with the appearance of a human on the throne high above.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 27, 'From what seemed to be His waist up, I saw a gleam like amber, with what looked like fire enclosing it all around. From what seemed to be His waist down, I also saw what looked like fire. There was a brilliant light all around Him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 1, 28, 'The appearance of the brilliant light all around was like that of a rainbow in a cloud on a rainy day. This was the appearance of the form of the LORD''s glory. When I saw [it], I fell facedown and heard a voice speaking.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 1, 'He said to me, "Son of man, stand up on your feet and I will speak with you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 2, 'As He spoke to me, the Spirit entered me and set me on my feet, and I listened to the One who was speaking to me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 3, 'He said to me: "Son of man, I am sending you to the Israelites [and] to the rebellious nations who have rebelled against Me. The Israelites and their ancestors have transgressed against Me to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 4, 'The children are obstinate and hardhearted. I am sending you to them, and you must say to them: This is what the Lord God says.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 5, 'Whether they listen or refuse [to listen]-- for they are a rebellious house-- they will know that a prophet has been among them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 6, '"But you, son of man, do not be afraid of them or their words, though briers and thorns are beside you and you live among scorpions. Don''t be afraid of their words or be discouraged by [the look on] their faces, for they are a rebellious house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 7, 'But speak My words to them whether they listen or refuse [to listen], for they are rebellious.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 8, '"And you, son of man, listen to what I tell you: Do not be rebellious like that rebellious house. Open your mouth and eat what I am giving you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 9, 'So I looked and saw a hand reaching out to me, and there was a written scroll in it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 2, 10, 'When He unrolled it before me, it was written on the front and back; [words of] lamentation, mourning, and woe were written on it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 1, 'He said to me: "Son of man, eat what you find [here]. Eat this scroll, then go and speak to the house of Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 2, 'So I opened my mouth, and He fed me the scroll.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 3, '"Son of man," he said to me, "eat and fill your stomach with this scroll I am giving you." So I ate [it], and it was as sweet as honey in my mouth.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 4, 'Then He said to me: "Son of man, go to the house of Israel and speak My words to them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 5, 'For you are not being sent to a people of unintelligible speech or difficult language but to the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 6, '[You are] not [being sent] to many peoples of unintelligible speech or difficult language, whose words you cannot understand. No doubt, if I sent you to them, they would listen to you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 7, 'But the house of Israel will not want to listen to you because they do not want to listen to Me. For the whole house of Israel is hardheaded and hardhearted.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 8, 'Look, I have made your face as hard as their faces and your forehead as hard as their foreheads.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 9, 'I have made your forehead like a diamond, harder than flint. Don''t be afraid of them or discouraged by [the look on] their faces, even though they are a rebellious house."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 10, 'Next He said to me: "Son of man, listen carefully to all My words that I speak to you and take [them] to heart.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 11, 'Go to your people, the exiles, and speak to them. Tell them: This is what the Lord God says, whether they listen or refuse [to listen]."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 12, 'The Spirit then lifted me up, and I heard a great rumbling sound behind me-- praise the glory of the LORD in His place!--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 13, 'with the sound of the living creatures'' wings brushing against each other and the sound of the wheels beside them, a great rumbling sound.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 14, 'So the Spirit lifted me up and took me away. I left in bitterness and in an angry spirit, and the LORD''s hand was on me powerfully.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 15, 'I came to the exiles at Tel-abib, who were living by the Chebar Canal, and I sat there stunned for seven days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 16, 'Now at the end of seven days the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 17, '"Son of man, I have made you a watchman over the house of Israel. When you hear a word from My mouth, give them a warning from Me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 18, 'If I say to the wicked person: You will surely die, but you do not warn him-- you don''t speak out to warn him about his wicked way in order to save his life-- that wicked person will die for his iniquity. Yet I will hold you responsible for his blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 19, 'But if you warn a wicked person and he does not turn from his wickedness or his wicked way, he will die for his iniquity, but you will have saved your life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 20, 'Now if a righteous person turns from his righteousness and practices iniquity, and I put a stumbling block in front of him, he will die. If you did not warn him, he will die because of his sin and the righteous acts he did will not be remembered. Yet I will hold you responsible for his blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 21, 'But if you warn the righteous person that he should not sin, and he does not sin, he will indeed live because he listened to [your] warning, and you will have saved your life."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 22, 'Then the hand of the LORD was on me there, and He said to me, "Get up, go out to the plain, and I will speak with you there."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 23, 'So I got up and went out to the plain. The LORD''s glory was present there, like the glory I had seen by the Chebar Canal, and I fell facedown.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 24, 'The Spirit entered me and set me on my feet. He spoke with me and said: "Go, shut yourself inside your house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 25, 'And you, son of man, they will put ropes on you and bind you with them so you cannot go out among them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 26, 'I will make your tongue stick to the roof of your mouth, and you will be mute and unable to rebuke them, for they are a rebellious house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 3, 27, 'But when I speak with you, I will open your mouth, and you will say to them: This is what the Lord God says. Let the one who listens, listen, and let the one who refuses, refuse-- for they are a rebellious house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 1, '"Now you, son of man, take a brick, set it in front of you, and draw the city of Jerusalem on it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 2, 'Then lay siege against it: construct a siege wall, build a ramp, pitch military camps, and place battering rams against it on all sides.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 3, 'Take an iron plate and set it up as an iron wall between yourself and the city. Turn your face toward it so that it is under siege, and besiege it. This will be a sign for the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 4, '"Then lie down on your left side and place the iniquity of the house of Israel on it. You will bear their iniquity for the number of days you lie on your side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 5, 'For I have assigned you the years of their iniquity according to the number of days [you lie down], 390 days; so you will bear the iniquity of the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 6, 'When you have completed these days, lie down again, but on your right side, and bear the iniquity of the house of Judah. I have assigned you 40 days, a day for each year.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 7, 'You must turn your face toward the siege of Jerusalem with your arm bared, and prophesy against it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 8, 'Be aware that I will put cords on you so you cannot turn from side to side until you have finished the days of your siege.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 9, '"Also take wheat, barley, beans, lentils, millet, and spelt. Put them in a single container and make them into bread for yourself. You are to eat it during the number of days you lie on your side, 390 days.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 10, 'The food you eat each day will be eight ounces by weight; you will eat it from time to time.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 11, 'You are also to drink water by measure, one-sixth of a gallon, [which] you will drink from time to time.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 12, 'You will eat it as [you would] a barley cake and bake it over dried human excrement in their sight."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 13, 'The LORD said, "This is how the Israelites will eat their bread-- ceremonially unclean-- among the nations where I will banish them."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 14, 'But I said, "Ah, Lord God, I have never been defiled. From my youth until now I have not eaten anything that died naturally or was mauled by wild beasts. And impure meat has never entered my mouth."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 15, 'He replied to me, "Look, I will let you [use] cow dung instead of human excrement, and you can make your bread over that."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 16, 'Then He said to me, "Son of man, I am going to cut off the supply of bread in Jerusalem. They will anxiously eat bread [rationed] by weight and in dread drink water by measure.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 4, 17, 'So they will lack bread and water; everyone will be devastated and waste away because of their iniquity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 1, '"Now you, son of man, take a sharp sword, use it as you would a barber''s razor, and shave your head and beard. Then take a pair of scales and divide the hair.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 2, 'You are to burn up one third [of it] in the city when the days of the siege have ended; you are to take one third and slash [it] with the sword all around the city; and you are to scatter one third to the wind, for I will draw a sword [to chase] after them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 3, 'But you are to take a few strands from the hair and secure them in the folds of your [robe].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 4, 'Take some more of them, throw them into the fire, and burn them in it. A fire will spread from it to the whole house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 5, '"This is what the Lord God says: I have set this Jerusalem in the center of the nations, with countries all around her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 6, 'But she has rebelled against My ordinances with more wickedness than the nations, and against My statutes more than the countries that surround her. For her people have rejected My ordinances and have not walked in My statutes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 7, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: Because you have been more insubordinate than the nations around you-- you have not walked in My statutes or kept My ordinances; you have not even kept the ordinances of the nations around you--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 8, 'therefore, this is what the Lord God says: See, I am against you, [Jerusalem], and I will execute judgments within you in the sight of the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 9, 'Because of all your abominations, I will do to you what I have never done before and what I will never do again.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 10, 'As a result, fathers will eat [their] sons within Jerusalem, and sons will eat their fathers. I will execute judgments against you and scatter all your survivors to every direction of the wind.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 11, '"Therefore, as I live"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "I am going to cut [you] off and show [you] no pity, because you have defiled My sanctuary with all your detestable practices and abominations. Yes, I will not spare [you].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 12, 'One third of your people will die by plague and be consumed by famine within you; one third will fall by the sword all around you; and I will scatter one third to every direction of the wind, and I will draw a sword [to chase] after them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 13, 'When My anger is spent and I have vented My wrath on them, I will be appeased. Then, after I have spent My wrath on them, they will know that I, the LORD, have spoken in My jealousy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 14, '"I will make you a ruin and a disgrace among the nations around you, in the sight of everyone who passes by.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 15, 'So you will be a disgrace and a taunt, a warning and a horror, to the nations around you when I execute judgments against you in anger, wrath, and furious rebukes. I, the LORD, have spoken.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 16, 'When I shoot deadly arrows of famine at them, arrows for destruction that I will send to destroy you, [inhabitants of Jerusalem], I will intensify the famine against you and cut off your supply of bread.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 5, 17, 'I will send famine and dangerous animals against you. They will leave you childless, [Jerusalem]. Plague and bloodshed will sweep through you, and I will bring a sword against you. I, the LORD, have spoken."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 2, '"Son of man, turn your face toward the mountains of Israel and prophesy against them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 3, 'You are to say: Mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord God! This is what the Lord God says to the mountains and the hills, to the ravines and the valleys: I am about to bring a sword against you, and I will destroy your high places.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 4, 'Your altars will be desolated and your incense altars smashed. I will throw down your slain in front of your idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 5, 'I will lay the corpses of the Israelites in front of their idols and scatter your bones around your altars.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 6, 'Wherever you live the cities will be in ruins and the high places will be desolate, so that your altars will lie in ruins and be desecrated, your idols smashed and obliterated, your incense altars cut down, and your works wiped out.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 7, 'The slain will fall among you, and you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 8, '"Yet I will leave a remnant when you are scattered among the nations, for throughout the countries there will be some of you who will escape the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 9, 'Then your survivors will remember Me among the nations where they are taken captive, how I was crushed by their promiscuous hearts that turned away from Me and by their eyes that lusted after their idols. They will loathe themselves because of the evil things they did, their abominations of every kind.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 10, 'And they will know that I am the LORD; I did not threaten to bring this disaster on them without a reason.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 11, '"This is what the Lord God says: Clap your hands, stamp your feet, and cry out over all the evil abominations of the house of Israel, who will fall by the sword, famine, and plague.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 12, 'The one who is far off will die by plague; the one who is near will fall by the sword; and the one who remains and is spared will die of famine. In this way I will exhaust My wrath on them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 13, 'You will [all] know that I am the LORD when their slain lie among their idols around their altars, on every high hill, on all the mountaintops, and under every green tree and every leafy oak-- the places where they offered pleasing aromas to all their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 6, 14, 'I will stretch out My hand against them, and wherever they live I will make the land a desolate waste, from the wilderness to Diblah. Then they will know that I am Yahweh."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 1, 'And the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 2, '"Son of man, this is what the Lord God says to the land of Israel: An end! The end has come on the four corners of the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 3, 'The end is now on you; I will send My anger against you and judge you according to your ways. I will punish you for all your abominations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 4, 'I will not look on you with pity or spare [you], but I will punish you for your ways and for your abominations within you. Then you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 5, 'This is what the Lord God says: Look, one disaster after another is coming!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 6, 'An end has come; the end has come! It has awakened against you. Look, it is coming!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 7, 'Doom has come on you, inhabitants of the land. The time has come; the day is near. There will be panic on the mountains and not celebration.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 8, 'I will pour out My wrath on you very soon; I will exhaust My anger against you and judge you according to your ways. I will punish you for all your abominations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 9, 'I will not look on [you] with pity or spare [you]. I will punish you for your ways and for your abominations within you. Then you will know that it is I, the LORD, who strikes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 10, 'Look, the day is coming! Doom has gone out. The rod has blossomed; arrogance has bloomed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 11, 'Violence has grown into a rod of wickedness; none of them [will remain]: none of their multitude, none of their wealth, and none of the eminent among them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 12, 'The time has come; the day has arrived. Let the buyer not rejoice and the seller not mourn, for wrath is on all her multitude.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 13, 'The seller will certainly not return to what was sold as long as he and the buyer remain alive. For the vision concerning all its people will not be revoked, and none of them will preserve his life because of his iniquity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 14, 'They have blown the trumpet and prepared everything, but no one goes to war, for My wrath is on all her multitude.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 15, 'The sword is on the outside; plague and famine are on the inside. Whoever is in the field will die by the sword, and famine and plague will devour whoever is in the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 16, 'The survivors among them will escape and live on the mountains like doves of the valley, all of them moaning, each over his own iniquity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 17, 'All their hands will become weak, and all [their] knees will turn to water.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 18, 'They will put on sackcloth, and horror will overwhelm them. Shame will cover all [their] faces, and all their heads will be bald.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 19, 'They will throw their silver into the streets, and their gold will seem like something filthy. Their silver and gold will be unable to save them in the day of the LORD''s wrath. They will not satisfy their appetites or fill their stomachs, for these were the stumbling blocks that brought about their iniquity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 20, 'He appointed His beautiful ornaments for majesty, but they made their abhorrent images from them, their detestable things. Therefore, I have made these into something filthy for them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 21, 'I will hand these things over to foreigners as plunder and to the wicked of the earth as spoil, and they will profane them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 22, 'I will turn My face from the wicked as they profane My treasured place. Violent men will enter it and profane it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 23, 'Forge the chain, for the land is filled with crimes of bloodshed, and the city is filled with violence.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 24, 'So I will bring the most evil of nations to take possession of their houses. I will put an end to the pride of the strong, and their sacred places will be profaned.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 25, 'Anguish is coming! They will seek peace, but there will be none.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 26, 'Disaster after disaster will come, and there will be rumor after rumor. Then they will seek a vision from a prophet, but instruction will perish from the priests and counsel from the elders.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 7, 27, 'The king will mourn; the prince will be clothed in grief; and the hands of the people of the land will tremble. I will deal with them according to their own conduct, and I will judge them by their own standards. Then they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 1, 'In the sixth year, in the sixth [month], on the fifth [day] of the month, I was sitting in my house and the elders of Judah were sitting in front of me, and there the hand of the Lord God came down on me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 2, 'I looked, and there was a form that had the appearance of a man. From what seemed to be His waist down was fire, and from His waist up was something that looked bright, like the gleam of amber.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 3, 'He stretched out what appeared to be a hand and took me by the hair of my head. Then the Spirit lifted me up between earth and heaven and carried me in visions of God to Jerusalem, to the entrance of the inner gate that faces north, where the offensive statue that provokes jealousy was located.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 4, 'I saw the glory of the God of Israel there, like the vision I had seen in the plain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 5, 'The LORD said to me, "Son of man, look toward the north." I looked to the north, and there was this offensive statue north of the altar gate, at the entrance.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 6, 'He said to me, "Son of man, do you see what they are doing, the great abominations that the house of Israel is committing here, so that I must depart from My sanctuary? You will see even greater abominations."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 7, 'Then He brought me to the entrance of the court, and when I looked there was a hole in the wall.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 8, 'He said to me, "Son of man, dig through the wall." So I dug through the wall, and there was a doorway.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 9, 'He said to me, "Go in and see the terrible abominations they are committing here."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 10, 'I went in and looked, and there engraved all around the wall was every form of detestable thing, crawling creatures and beasts, as well as all the idols of the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 11, 'Seventy elders from the house of Israel were standing before them, with Jaazaniah son of Shaphan standing among them. Each had an incense burner in his hand, and a fragrant cloud of incense was rising up.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 12, 'Then He said to me, "Son of man, do you see what the elders of the house of Israel are doing in the darkness, each at the shrine of his idol? For they are saying: The LORD does not see us. The LORD has abandoned the land."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 13, 'Again He said to me, "You will see even greater abominations, which they are committing."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 14, 'So He brought me to the entrance of the north gate of the LORD''s house, and I saw women sitting there weeping for Tammuz.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 15, 'And He said to me, "Do you see [this], son of man? You will see even greater abominations than these."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 16, 'So He brought me to the inner court of the LORD''s house, and there were about 25 men at the entrance of the LORD''s temple, between the portico and the altar, with their backs to the LORD''s temple and their faces [turned] to the east. They were bowing to the east in worship of the sun.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 17, 'And He said to me, "Do you see [this], son of man? Is it not enough for the house of Judah to commit the abominations they are practicing here, that they must also fill the land with violence and repeatedly provoke Me to anger, even putting the branch to their nose?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 8, 18, 'Therefore I will respond with wrath. I will not show pity or spare [them]. Though they cry out in My ears with a loud voice, I will not listen to them."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 1, 'Then He called to me directly with a loud voice, "Come near, executioners of the city, each [of you] with a destructive weapon in his hand."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 2, 'And I saw six men coming from the direction of the Upper Gate, which faces north, each with a war club in his hand. There was another man among them, clothed in linen, with writing equipment at his side. They came and stood beside the bronze altar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 3, 'Then the glory of the God of Israel rose from above the cherubim where it had been, to the threshold of the temple. He called to the man clothed in linen with the writing equipment at his side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 4, '"Pass throughout the city of Jerusalem," the LORD said to him, "and put a mark on the foreheads of the men who sigh and groan over all the abominations committed in it."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 5, 'To the others He said in my hearing, "Pass through the city after him and start killing; do not show pity or spare [them]!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 6, 'Slaughter the old men, the young men and women, as well as the [older] women and little children, but do not come near anyone who has the mark. Now begin at My sanctuary." So they began with the elders who were in front of the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 7, 'Then He said to them, "Defile the temple and fill the courts with the slain. Go!" So they went out killing [people] in the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 8, 'While they were killing, I was left alone. And I fell facedown and cried out, "Ah, Lord God! Are You going to destroy the entire remnant of Israel when You pour out Your wrath on Jerusalem?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 9, 'He answered me: "The iniquity of the house of Israel and Judah is extremely great; the land is full of bloodshed, and the city full of perversity. For they say: The LORD has abandoned the land; He does not see.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 10, 'But as for Me, I will not show pity or spare [them]. I will bring their actions down on their own heads."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 9, 11, 'Then the man clothed in linen with the writing equipment at his side reported back, "I have done as You commanded me."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 1, 'Then I looked, and there above the expanse over the heads of the cherubim was something like sapphire stone resembling the shape of a throne that appeared above them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 2, 'The LORD spoke to the man clothed in linen and said, "Go inside the wheelwork beneath the cherubim. Fill your hands with hot coals from among the cherubim and scatter [them] over the city." So he went in as I watched.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 3, 'Now the cherubim were standing to the south of the temple when the man went in, and the cloud filled the inner court.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 4, 'Then the glory of the LORD rose from above the cherubim to the threshold of the temple. The temple was filled with the cloud, and the court was filled with the brightness of the LORD''s glory.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 5, 'The sound of the cherubim''s wings could be heard as far as the outer court; it was like the voice of God Almighty when He speaks.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 6, 'After the LORD commanded the man clothed in linen, saying, "Take fire from inside the wheelwork, from among the cherubim," the man went in and stood beside a wheel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 7, 'Then one of the cherubim reached out his hand to the fire that was among them. He took [some], and put [it] into the hands of the man clothed in linen, who took it and went out.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 8, 'The cherubim appeared to have the form of human hands under their wings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 9, 'I looked, and there were four wheels beside the cherubim, one wheel beside each cherub. The luster of the wheels was like the gleam of beryl.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 10, 'In appearance, all four had the same form, like a wheel within a wheel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 11, 'When they moved, they would go in any of the four directions, without pivoting as they moved. But wherever the head faced, they would go in that direction, without pivoting as they went.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 12, 'Their entire bodies, including their backs, hands, wings, and the wheels that the four of them had, were full of eyes all around.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 13, 'As I listened the wheels were called "the wheelwork."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 14, 'Each one had four faces: the first face was that of a cherub, the second that of a man, the third that of a lion, and the fourth that of an eagle.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 15, 'The cherubim ascended; these were the living creatures I had seen by the Chebar Canal.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 16, 'When the cherubim moved, the wheels moved beside them, and when they lifted their wings to rise from the earth, even then the wheels did not veer away from them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 17, 'When the cherubim stood still, the wheels stood still, and when they ascended, the wheels ascended with them, for the spirit of the living creatures was in them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 18, 'Then the glory of the LORD moved away from the threshold of the temple and stood above the cherubim.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 19, 'The cherubim lifted their wings and ascended from the earth right before my eyes; the wheels were beside them as they went. The glory of the God of Israel was above them, and it stood at the entrance to the eastern gate of the LORD''s house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 20, 'These were the living creatures I had seen beneath the God of Israel by the Chebar Canal, and I recognized that they were cherubim.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 21, 'Each had four faces and each had four wings, with the form of human hands under their wings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 10, 22, 'Their faces looked like the same faces I had seen by the Chebar Canal. Each creature went straight ahead.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 1, 'The Spirit then lifted me up and brought me to the eastern gate of the LORD''s house, which faces east, and at the gate''s entrance were 25 men. Among them I saw Jaazaniah son of Azzur, and Pelatiah son of Benaiah, leaders of the people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 2, 'The LORD said to me, "Son of man, these are the men who plan evil and give wicked advice in this city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 3, 'They are saying: Isn''t the time near to build houses? The city is the pot, and we are the meat.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 4, 'Therefore, prophesy against them. Prophesy, son of man!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 5, 'Then the Spirit of the LORD came on me, and He told me, "You are to say: This is what the LORD says: That is what you are thinking, house of Israel; and I know the thoughts that arise in your mind.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 6, 'You have multiplied your slain in this city, filling its streets with the dead.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 7, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: The slain you have put within it are the meat, and the city is the pot, but I will remove you from it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 8, 'You fear the sword, so I will bring the sword against you." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 9, '"I will bring you out of the city and hand you over to foreigners; I will execute judgments against you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 10, 'You will fall by the sword, and I will judge you at the border of Israel. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 11, 'The city will not be a pot for you, and you will not be the meat within it. I will judge you at the border of Israel,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 12, 'so you will know that I am the LORD, whose statutes you have not followed and whose ordinances you have not practiced. Instead, you have acted according to the ordinances of the nations around you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 13, 'Now while I was prophesying, Pelatiah son of Benaiah died. Then I fell facedown and cried out with a loud voice: "Ah, Lord God! Will You bring to an end the remnant of Israel?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 14, 'The word of the LORD came to me again:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 15, '"Son of man, your own relatives, those who have the right to redeem you,and the entire house of Israel, all of them, are those the residents of Jerusalem have said this to: Stay away from the LORD; this land has been given to us as a possession.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 16, '"Therefore say: This is what the Lord God says: Though I sent them far away among the nations and scattered them among the countries, yet for a little while I have been a sanctuary for them in the countries where they have gone.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 17, '"Therefore say: This is what the Lord God says: I will gather you from the peoples and assemble you from the countries where you have been scattered, and I will give you the land of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 18, '"When they arrive there, they will remove all its detestable things and all its abominations from it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 19, 'And I will give them one heart and put a new spirit within them; I will remove their heart of stone from their bodies and give them a heart of flesh,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 20, 'so they may follow My statutes, keep My ordinances, and practice them. Then they will be My people, and I will be their God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 21, 'But as for those whose hearts pursue their desire for detestable things and abominations, I will bring their actions down on their own heads." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 22, 'Then the cherubim, with the wheels beside them, lifted their wings, and the glory of the God of Israel was above them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 23, 'The glory of the LORD rose up from within the city and stood on the mountain east of the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 24, 'The Spirit lifted me up and brought me to Chaldea and to the exiles in a vision from the Spirit of God. After the vision I had seen left me,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 11, 25, 'I spoke to the exiles about all the things the LORD had shown me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 2, '"Son of man, you are living among a rebellious house. They have eyes to see but do not see, and ears to hear but do not hear, for they are a rebellious house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 3, '"Son of man, pack your bags for exile and go into exile in their sight during the day. You will go into exile from your place to another place while they watch; perhaps they will understand, though they are a rebellious house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 4, 'During the day, bring out your bags like an exile''s bags while they look on. Then in the evening go out in their sight like those going into exile.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 5, 'As they watch, dig through the wall and take the [bags] out through it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 6, 'And while they look on, lift [the bags] to [your] shoulder and take [them] out in the dark; cover your face so that you cannot see the land. For I have made you a sign to the house of Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 7, 'So I did just as I was commanded. I brought out my bags like an exile''s bags in the daytime. In the evening I dug through the wall by hand; I took [them] out in the dark, carrying [them] on my shoulder in their sight.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 8, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me in the morning:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 9, '"Son of man, hasn''t the house of Israel, that rebellious house, asked you: What are you doing?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 10, 'Say to them: This is what the Lord God says: This oracle is about the prince in Jerusalem and all the house of Israel who are living there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 11, 'You are to say: I am a sign for you. Just as I have done, so it will be done to them; they will go into exile, into captivity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 12, 'The prince who is among them will lift [his bags] to his shoulder in the dark and go out. They will dig through the wall to bring [him] out through it. He will cover his face so he cannot see the land with his eyes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 13, 'But I will spread My net over him, and he will be caught in My snare. I will bring him to Babylon, the land of the Chaldeans, yet he will not see it, and he will die there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 14, 'I will also scatter all the attendants who surround him and all his troops to every direction of the wind, and I will draw a sword [to chase] after them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 15, 'They will know that I am the LORD when I disperse them among the nations and scatter them among the countries.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 16, 'But I will spare a few of them from the sword, famine, and plague so they can tell about all their abominations among the nations where they go. Then they will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 17, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 18, '"Son of man, eat your bread with trembling and drink your water with shaking and anxiety.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 19, 'Then say to the people of the land: This is what the Lord God says about the residents of Jerusalem in the land of Israel: They will eat their bread with anxiety and drink their water in dread, for their land will be stripped of everything in it because of the violence of all who live there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 20, 'The inhabited cities will be destroyed, and the land will become a desolation. Then you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 21, 'Again the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 22, '"Son of man, what is this proverb you [people] have about the land of Israel, which goes: The days keep passing by, and every vision fails?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 23, 'Therefore say to them: This is what the Lord God says: I will put a stop to this proverb, and they will not use it again in Israel. But say to them: The days draw near, as well as the fulfillment of every vision.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 24, 'For there will no longer be any false vision or flattering divination within the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 25, 'But I, the LORD, will speak whatever message I will speak, and it will be done. It will no longer be delayed. For in your days, rebellious house, I will speak a message and bring it to pass." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 26, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 27, '"Son of man, notice that the house of Israel is saying: The vision that he sees concerns many years [from now]; he prophesies about distant times.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 12, 28, 'Therefore say to them: This is what the Lord God says: None of My words will be delayed any longer. The message I speak will be fulfilled." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 2, '"Son of man, prophesy against the prophets of Israel who are prophesying. Say to those who prophesy out of their own imagination: Hear the word of the LORD!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 3, 'This is what the Lord God says: Woe to the foolish prophets who follow their own spirit and have seen nothing.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 4, 'Your prophets, Israel, are like jackals among ruins.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 5, 'You did not go up to the gaps or restore the wall around the house of Israel so that it might stand in battle on the day of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 6, 'They see false visions and speak lying divinations. They claim: [This is] the LORD''s declaration, when the LORD did not send them, yet they wait for the fulfillment of [their] message.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 7, 'Didn''t you see a false vision and speak a lying divination when you proclaimed: [This is] the LORD''s declaration, even though I had not spoken?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 8, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: I am against you because you have spoken falsely and had lying visions." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 9, '"My hand will be against the prophets who see false visions and speak lying divinations. They will not be present in the fellowship of My people or be recorded in the register of the house of Israel, and they will not enter the land of Israel. Then you will know that I am the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 10, '"Since they have led My people astray saying: Peace, when there is no peace, for when someone builds a wall they plaster it with whitewash,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 11, 'therefore, tell those who plaster [it] that it will fall. Torrential rain will come, and I will send hailstones plunging down, and a windstorm will be released.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 12, 'Now when the wall has fallen, will you not be asked: Where is the coat of whitewash that you put on [it]?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 13, '"So this is what the Lord God says: I will release a windstorm in My wrath. Torrential rain will come in My anger, and hailstones [will fall] in destructive fury.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 14, 'I will tear down the wall you plastered with whitewash and knock it to the ground so that its foundation is exposed. The city will fall, and you will be destroyed within it. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 15, 'After I exhaust My wrath against the wall and against those who plaster it with whitewash, I will say to you: The wall is no more and neither are those who plastered it--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 16, 'those prophets of Israel who prophesied to Jerusalem and saw a vision of peace for her when there was no peace." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 17, '"Now, son of man, turn toward the women of your people who prophesy out of their own imagination. Prophesy against them');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 18, 'and say: This is what the Lord God says: Woe to the women who sew [magic] bands on the wrist of every hand and who make veils for the heads of people of every height in order to ensnare lives. Will you ensnare the lives of My people but preserve your own?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 19, 'You profane Me in front of My people for handfuls of barley and scraps of bread; you kill those who should not die and spare those who should not live, when you lie to My people, who listen to lies.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 20, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: I am against your [magic] bands that you ensnare people with like birds, and I will tear them from your arms. I will free the people you have ensnared like birds.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 21, 'I will also tear off your veils and deliver My people from your hands, so that they will no longer be prey in your hands. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 22, 'Because you have disheartened the righteous person with lies, even though I have not caused him grief, and because you have encouraged the wicked person not to turn from his evil way to save his life,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 13, 23, 'therefore you will no longer see false visions or practice divination. I will deliver My people from your hands. Then you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 1, 'Some of the elders of Israel came to me and sat down in front of me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 2, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 3, '"Son of man, these men have set up idols in their hearts and have put sinful stumbling blocks before their faces. Should I be consulted by them at all?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 4, '"Therefore, speak to them and tell them: This is what the Lord God says: When anyone from the house of Israel sets up idols in his heart, puts a sinful stumbling block before his face, and then comes to the prophet, I, the LORD, will answer him appropriately. [I will answer him] according to his many idols,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 5, 'so that I may take hold of the house of Israel by their hearts, because they are all estranged from Me by their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 6, '"Therefore, say to the house of Israel: This is what the Lord God says: Repent and turn away from your idols; turn your faces away from all your abominations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 7, 'For when anyone from the house of Israel or from the foreigners who reside in Israel separates himself from Me, setting up idols in his heart and putting a sinful stumbling block before his face, and then comes to the prophet to inquire of Me, I, the LORD, will answer him Myself.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 8, 'I will turn against that one and make him a sign and a proverb; I will cut him off from among My people. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 9, '"But if the prophet is deceived and speaks a message, it was I, the LORD, who deceived that prophet. I will stretch out My hand against him and destroy him from among My people Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 10, 'They will bear their punishment-- the punishment of the one who inquires will be the same as that of the prophet--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 11, 'in order that the house of Israel may no longer stray from following Me and no longer defile themselves with all their transgressions. Then they will be My people and I will be their God." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 12, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 13, '"Son of man, if a land sins against Me by acting faithlessly, and I stretch out My hand against it to cut off its supply of bread, to send famine through it, and to wipe out [both] man and animal from it,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 14, 'even [if] these three men-- Noah, Daniel, and Job-- were in it, they would deliver [only] themselves by their righteousness." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 15, '"If I allow dangerous animals to pass through the land and depopulate it so that it becomes desolate, with no one passing through [it] for [fear of] the animals,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 16, 'even [if] these three men were in it, as I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "they could not deliver [their] sons or daughters. They alone would be delivered, but the land would be desolate.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 17, '"Or if I bring a sword against that land and say: Let a sword pass through it, so that I wipe out [both] man and animal from it,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 18, 'even [if] these three men were in it, as I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "they could not deliver [their] sons or daughters, but they alone would be delivered.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 19, '"Or if I send a plague into that land and pour out My wrath on it with bloodshed to wipe out [both] man and animal from it,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 20, 'even [if] Noah, Daniel, and Job were in it, as I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "they could not deliver [their] son or daughter. They would deliver [only] themselves by their righteousness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 21, '"For this is what the Lord God says: How much worse will it be when I send My four devastating judgments against Jerusalem-- sword, famine, dangerous animals, and plague-- in order to wipe out [both] man and animal from it!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 22, 'Even so, there will be survivors left in it, sons and daughters who will be brought out. Indeed, they will come out to you, and you will observe their conduct and actions. Then you will be consoled about the devastation I have brought on Jerusalem, about all I have brought on it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 14, 23, 'They will bring you consolation when you see their conduct and actions, and you will know that it was not without cause that I have done what I did to it." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 1, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 2, '"Son of man, how does the wood of the vine, that branch among the trees of the forest, compare to any other wood?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 3, 'Can wood be taken from it to make something useful? Or can anyone make a peg from it to hang things on?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 4, 'In fact, it is put into the fire as fuel. The fire devours both of its ends, and the middle is charred. Can it be useful for anything?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 5, 'Even when it was whole it could not be made into a useful object. How much less can it ever be made into anything useful when the fire has devoured it and it is charred!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 6, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: Like the wood of the vine among the trees of the forest, which I have given to the fire as fuel, so I will give up the residents of Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 7, 'I will turn against them. They may have escaped from the fire, but it will [still] consume them. And you will know that I am the LORD when I turn against them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 15, 8, 'I will make the land desolate because they have acted unfaithfully." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me again:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 2, '"Son of man, explain Jerusalem''s abominations to her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 3, 'You are to say: This is what the Lord God says to Jerusalem: Your origin and your birth were in the land of the Canaanites. Your father was an Amorite and your mother a Hittite.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 4, 'As for your birth, your umbilical cord wasn''t cut on the day you were born, and you weren''t washed clean with water. You were not rubbed with salt or wrapped in cloths.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 5, 'No one cared [enough] about you to do even one of these things out of compassion for you. But you were thrown out into the open field because you were despised on the day you were born.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 6, '"I passed by you and saw you lying in your blood, and I said to you [as you lay] in your blood: Live! Yes, I said to you [as you lay] in your blood: Live!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 7, 'I made you thrive like plants of the field. You grew up and matured and became very beautiful. Your breasts were formed and your hair grew, but you were stark naked.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 8, '"Then I passed by you and saw you, and you were indeed at the age for love. So I spread the edge of My garment over you and covered your nakedness. I pledged Myself to you, entered into a covenant with you, and you became Mine." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 9, '"I washed you with water, rinsed off your blood, and anointed you with oil.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 10, 'I clothed you in embroidered cloth and provided you with leather sandals. I also wrapped you in fine linen and covered you with silk.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 11, 'I adorned you with jewelry, putting bracelets on your wrists and a chain around your neck.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 12, 'I put a ring in your nose, earrings on your ears, and a beautiful tiara on your head.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 13, 'So you were adorned with gold and silver, and your clothing was [made] of fine linen, silk, and embroidered cloth. You ate fine flour, honey, and oil. You became extremely beautiful and attained royalty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 14, 'Your fame spread among the nations because of your beauty, for it was perfect through My splendor, which I had bestowed on you." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 15, '"But you were confident in your beauty and acted like a prostitute because of your fame. You lavished your sexual favors on everyone who passed by. Your beauty became his.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 16, 'You took some of your garments and made colorful high places for yourself, and you engaged in prostitution on them. These places should not have been built, and this should never have happened!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 17, 'You also took your beautiful jewelry made from the gold and silver I had given you, and you made male images so that you could engage in prostitution with them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 18, 'Then you took your embroidered garments to cover them, and set My oil and incense before them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 19, 'You also set before them as a pleasing aroma the food I gave you-- the fine flour, oil, and honey that I fed you. That is what happened." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 20, '"You even took your sons and daughters you bore to Me and sacrificed them to these images as food. Wasn''t your prostitution enough?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 21, 'You slaughtered My children and gave them up when you passed them through [the fire] to the images.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 22, 'In all your abominations and acts of prostitution, you did not remember the days of your youth when you were stark naked and lying in your blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 23, '"Then after all your evil-- Woe, woe to you!"-- the declaration of the Lord God--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 24, '"you built yourself a mound and made yourself an elevated place in every square.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 25, 'You built your elevated place at the head of every street and turned your beauty into an abomination. You spread your legs to everyone who passed by and increased your prostitution.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 26, 'You engaged in promiscuous acts with Egyptian men, your well-endowed neighbors, and increased your prostitution to provoke Me to anger.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 27, '"Therefore, I stretched out My hand against you and reduced your provisions. I gave you over to the desire of those who hate you, the Philistine women, who were embarrassed by your indecent behavior.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 28, 'Then you engaged in prostitution with the Assyrian men because you were not satisfied. Even though you did this with them, you were still not satisfied.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 29, 'So you extended your prostitution to Chaldea, the land of merchants, but you were not even satisfied with this!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 30, '"How your heart was inflamed [with lust]"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "when you did all these things, the acts of a brazen prostitute,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 31, 'building your mound at the head of every street and making your elevated place in every square. But you were unlike a prostitute because you scorned payment.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 32, 'You adulterous wife, who receives strangers instead of her husband!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 33, 'Men give gifts to all prostitutes, but you gave gifts to all your lovers. You bribed them to come to you from all around for your sexual favors.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 34, 'So you were the opposite of other women in your acts of prostitution; no one solicited you. When you paid a fee instead of one being paid to you, you were the opposite.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 35, '"Therefore, you prostitute, hear the word of the LORD!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 36, 'This is what the Lord God says: Because your lust was poured out and your nakedness exposed by your acts of prostitution with your lovers, and because of all your detestable idols and the blood of your children that you gave to them,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 37, 'I am therefore going to gather all the lovers you pleased-- all those you loved as well as all those you hated. I will gather them against you from all around and expose your nakedness to them so they see you completely naked.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 38, 'I will judge you the way adulteresses and those who shed blood are judged. Then I will bring about your bloodshed in wrath and jealousy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 39, 'I will hand you over to them, and they will level your mounds and tear down your elevated places. They will strip off your clothes, take your beautiful jewelry, and leave you stark naked.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 40, 'They will bring a mob against you to stone you and cut you to pieces with their swords.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 41, 'Then they will burn down your houses and execute judgments against you in the sight of many women. I will stop you from being a prostitute, and you will never again pay fees for lovers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 42, 'So I will satisfy My wrath against you, and My jealousy will turn away from you. Then I will be silent and no longer angry.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 43, 'Because you did not remember the days of your youth but enraged Me with all these things, I will also bring your actions down on your own head." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God. "Haven''t you committed immoral acts in addition to all your abominations?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 44, '"Look, everyone who uses proverbs will say this proverb about you: Like mother, like daughter.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 45, 'You are the daughter of your mother, who despised her husband and children. You are the sister of your sisters, who despised their husbands and children. Your mother was a Hittite and your father an Amorite.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 46, 'Your older sister was Samaria, who lived with her daughters to the north of you, and your younger sister was Sodom, who lived with her daughters to the south of you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 47, 'Didn''t you walk in their ways and practice their abominations? It was only a short time before you behaved more corruptly than they did.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 48, '"As I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "your sister Sodom and her daughters have not behaved as you and your daughters have.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 49, 'Now this was the iniquity of your sister Sodom: she and her daughters had pride, plenty of food, and comfortable security, but didn''t support the poor and needy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 50, 'They were haughty and did detestable things before Me, so I removed them when I saw [this].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 51, 'But Samaria did not commit [even] half your sins. You have multiplied your abominations beyond theirs and made your sisters appear righteous by all the abominations you have committed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 52, 'You must also bear your disgrace, since you have been an advocate for your sisters. For they appear more righteous than you because of your sins, which you committed more abhorrently than they [did]. So you also, be ashamed and bear your disgrace, since you have made your sisters appear righteous.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 53, '"I will restore their fortunes, the fortunes of Sodom and her daughters and those of Samaria and her daughters. I will also restore your fortunes among them,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 54, 'so you will bear your disgrace and be ashamed of all you did when you comforted them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 55, 'As for your sisters, Sodom and her daughters and Samaria and her daughters will return to their former state. You and your daughters will also return to your former state.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 56, 'Didn''t you treat your sister Sodom as an object of scorn when you were proud,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 57, 'before your wickedness was exposed? It was like the time you were scorned by the daughters of Aram and all those around her, and by the daughters of the Philistines-- those who treated you with contempt from every side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 58, 'You yourself must bear the consequences of your indecency and abominations"-- the LORD''s declaration.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 59, '"For this is what the Lord God says: I will deal with you according to what you have done, since you have despised the oath by breaking the covenant.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 60, 'But I will remember the covenant I made with you in the days of your youth, and I will establish an everlasting covenant with you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 61, 'Then you will remember your ways and be ashamed when you receive your older and younger sisters. I will give them to you as daughters, but not because of your covenant.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 62, 'I will establish My covenant with you, and you will know that I am the LORD,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 16, 63, 'so that when I make atonement for all you have done, you will remember and be ashamed, and never open your mouth again because of your disgrace." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 2, '"Son of man, pose a riddle and speak a parable to the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 3, 'You are to say: This is what the Lord God says: A great eagle with great wings, long pinions, and full plumage of many colors came to Lebanon and took the top of the cedar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 4, 'He plucked off its topmost shoot, brought it to the land of merchants, and set it in a city of traders.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 5, 'Then he took some of the land''s seed and put it in a fertile field; he set it [like] a willow, a plant by abundant waters.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 6, 'It sprouted and became a spreading vine, low in height with its branches turned toward him, yet its roots stayed under it. So it became a vine, produced branches, and sent forth shoots.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 7, 'But there was another great eagle with great wings and thick plumage. And this vine bent its roots toward him! It stretched out its branches to him from its planting bed, so that he might water it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 8, 'It had been planted in a good field by abundant waters in order to produce branches, bear fruit, and become a splendid vine.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 9, 'You are to say: This is what the Lord God says: Will it flourish? Will he not tear out its roots and strip off its fruit so that it shrivels? All its fresh leaves will wither! Great strength and many people will not be needed to pull it from its roots.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 10, 'Even though it is planted, will it flourish? Won''t it completely wither when the east wind strikes it? It will wither on the bed where it sprouted."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 11, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 12, '"Now say to that rebellious house: Don''t you know what these things mean? Tell [them]: The king of Babylon came to Jerusalem, took its king and officials, and brought them back with him to Babylon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 13, 'He took one of the royal family and made a covenant with him, putting him under oath. Then he took away the leading men of the land,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 14, 'so the kingdom might be humble and not exalt itself but might keep his covenant in order to endure.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 15, 'However, this king revolted against him by sending his ambassadors to Egypt so they might give him horses and a large army. Will he flourish? Will the one who does such things escape? Can he break a covenant and [still] escape?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 16, '"As I live"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "he will die in Babylon, in the land of the king who put him on the throne, whose oath he despised and whose covenant he broke.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 17, 'Pharaoh will not help him with [his] great army and vast horde in battle, when ramps are built and siege walls constructed to destroy many lives.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 18, 'He despised the oath by breaking the covenant. He did all these things even though he gave his hand [in pledge]. He will not escape!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 19, 'Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: "As I live, I will bring down on his head My oath that he despised and My covenant that he broke.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 20, 'I will spread My net over him, and he will be captured in My snare. I will bring him to Babylon and execute judgment on him there for the treachery he committed against Me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 21, 'All the fugitives among his troops will fall by the sword, and those who survive will be scattered to every direction of the wind. Then you will know that I, Yahweh, have spoken."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 22, 'This is what the Lord God says: I will take [a sprig] from the lofty top of the cedar and plant [it]. I will pluck a tender sprig from its topmost shoots, and I will plant [it] on a high towering mountain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 23, 'I will plant it on Israel''s high mountain so that it may bear branches, produce fruit, and become a majestic cedar. Birds of every kind will nest under it, taking shelter in the shade of its branches.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 17, 24, 'Then all the trees of the field will know that I am the LORD. I bring down the tall tree, and make the low tree tall. I cause the green tree to wither and make the withered tree thrive. I, Yahweh, have spoken and I will do [it].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 2, '"What do you mean by using this proverb concerning the land of Israel: The fathers eat sour grapes, and the children''s teeth are set on edge?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 3, 'As I live"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "you will no longer use this proverb in Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 4, 'Look, every life belongs to Me. The life of the father is like the life of the son-- both belong to Me. The person who sins is the one who will die.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 5, '"Now suppose a man is righteous and does what is just and right:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 6, 'He does not eat at the mountain [shrines] or raise his eyes to the idols of the house of Israel. He does not defile his neighbor''s wife or come near a woman during her menstrual impurity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 7, 'He doesn''t oppress anyone but returns his collateral to the debtor. He does not commit robbery, but gives his bread to the hungry and covers the naked with clothing.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 8, 'He doesn''t lend at interest or for profit but keeps his hand from wrongdoing and carries out true justice between men.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 9, 'He follows My statutes and keeps My ordinances, acting faithfully. Such a person is righteous; he will certainly live." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 10, '"Now suppose the man has a violent son, who sheds blood and does any of these [things],');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 11, 'though the father has done none of them. Indeed, when the son eats at the mountain [shrines] and defiles his neighbor''s wife,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 12, 'and [when] he oppresses the poor and needy, commits robbery, and does not return collateral, and [when] he raises his eyes to the idols, commits abominations,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 13, 'and lends at interest or for profit, will he live? He will not live! Since he has committed all these abominations, he will certainly die. His blood will be on him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 14, '"Now suppose he has a son who sees all the sins his father has committed, and though he sees them, he does not do likewise.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 15, 'He does not eat at the mountain [shrines] or raise his eyes to the idols of the house of Israel. He does not defile his neighbor''s wife.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 16, 'He doesn''t oppress anyone, hold collateral, or commit robbery. He gives his bread to the hungry and covers the naked with clothing.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 17, 'He keeps his hand from [harming] the poor, not taking interest or profit [on a loan]. He practices My ordinances and follows My statutes. Such a person will not die for his father''s iniquity. He will certainly live.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 18, '"As for his father, he will die for his own iniquity because he practiced fraud, robbed [his] brother, and did what was wrong among his people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 19, 'But you may ask: Why doesn''t the son suffer punishment for the father''s iniquity? Since the son has done what is just and right, carefully observing all My statues, he will certainly live.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 20, 'The person who sins is the one who will die. A son won''t suffer punishment for the father''s iniquity, and a father won''t suffer punishment for the son''s iniquity. The righteousness of the righteous person will be on him, and the wickedness of the wicked person will be on him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 21, '"Now if the wicked person turns from all the sins he has committed, keeps all My statutes, and does what is just and right, he will certainly live; he will not die.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 22, 'None of the transgressions he has committed will be held against him. He will live because of the righteousness he has practiced.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 23, 'Do I take any pleasure in the death of the wicked?" [This is] the declaration of the Lord God. "Instead, don''t I [take pleasure] when he turns from his ways and lives?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 24, 'But when a righteous person turns from his righteousness and practices iniquity, committing the same abominations that the wicked do, will he live? None of the righteous acts he did will be remembered. He will die because of the treachery he has engaged in and the sin he has committed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 25, '"But you say: The Lord''s way isn''t fair. Now listen, house of Israel: Is it My way that is unfair? Instead, isn''t it your ways that are unfair?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 26, 'When a righteous person turns from his righteousness and practices iniquity, he will die for this. He will die because of the iniquity he has practiced.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 27, 'But if a wicked person turns from the wickedness he has committed and does what is just and right, he will preserve his life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 28, 'He will certainly live because he thought it over and turned from all the transgressions he had committed; he will not die.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 29, 'But the house of Israel says: The Lord''s way isn''t fair. Is it My ways that are unfair, house of Israel? Instead, isn''t it your ways that are unfair?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 30, '"Therefore, house of Israel, I will judge each one of you according to his ways." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God. "Repent and turn from all your transgressions, so they will not be a stumbling block that causes your punishment.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 31, 'Throw off all the transgressions you have committed, and make yourselves a new heart and a new spirit. Why should you die, house of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 18, 32, 'For I take no pleasure in anyone''s death." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God. "So repent and live!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 1, '"Now, lament for the princes of Israel');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 2, 'and say: What was your mother? A lioness! She lay down among the lions; she reared her cubs among the young lions.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 3, 'She brought up one of her cubs, and he became a young lion. After he learned to tear prey, he devoured people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 4, 'When the nations heard about him, he was caught in their pit. Then they led him away with hooks to the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 5, 'When she saw that she waited [in vain], that her hope was lost, she took another of her cubs and made him a young lion.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 6, 'He prowled among the lions, and he became a young lion. After he learned to tear prey, he devoured people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 7, 'He devastated their strongholds and destroyed their cities. The land and everything in it shuddered at the sound of his roaring.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 8, 'Then the nations from the surrounding provinces set out against him. They spread their net over him; he was caught in their pit.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 9, 'They put a wooden yoke on him with hooks and led him away to the king of Babylon. They brought him into the fortresses so his roar could no longer be heard on the mountains of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 10, 'Your mother was like a vine in your vineyard, planted by the water; it was fruitful and full of branches because of plentiful waters.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 11, 'It had strong branches, [fit] for the scepters of rulers; its height towered among the clouds. So it was conspicuous for its height as well as its many branches.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 12, 'But it was uprooted in fury, thrown to the ground, and the east wind dried up its fruit. Its strong branches were torn off and dried up; fire consumed them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 13, 'Now it is planted in the wilderness, in a dry and thirsty land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 19, 14, 'Fire has gone out from its main branch and has devoured its fruit, so that it no longer has a strong branch, a scepter for ruling. This is a lament and should be used as a lament."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 1, 'In the seventh year, in the fifth [month], on the tenth [day] of the month, some of Israel''s elders came to consult the LORD, and they sat down in front of me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 2, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 3, '"Son of man, speak with the elders of Israel and tell them: This is what the Lord God says: Are you coming to consult Me? As I live, I will not be consulted by you." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 4, '"Will you pass judgment against them, will you pass judgment, son of man? Explain to them the abominations of their fathers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 5, 'Say to them: This is what the Lord God says: On the day I chose Israel, I swore an oath to the descendants of Jacob''s house and made Myself known to them in the land of Egypt. I swore to them, saying: I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 6, 'On that day I swore to them that I would bring them out of the land of Egypt into a land I had searched out for them, [a land] flowing with milk and honey, the most beautiful of all lands.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 7, 'I also said to them: Each of you must throw away the detestable things that are before your eyes and not defile yourselves with the idols of Egypt. I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 8, '"But they rebelled against Me and were unwilling to listen to Me. None of them threw away the detestable things that were before their eyes, and they did not forsake the idols of Egypt. So I considered pouring out My wrath on them, exhausting My anger against them within the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 9, 'But I acted for the sake of My name, so that it would not be profaned in the eyes of the nations they were living among, in whose sight I had made Myself known to Israel by bringing them out of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 10, '"So I brought them out of the land of Egypt and led them into the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 11, 'Then I gave them My statutes and explained My ordinances to them-- the person who does them will live by them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 12, 'I also gave them My Sabbaths to serve as a sign between Me and them, so they will know that I am the LORD who sets them apart as holy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 13, '"But the house of Israel rebelled against Me in the wilderness. They did not follow My statutes and they rejected My ordinances-- the person who does them will live by them. They also completely profaned My Sabbaths. So I considered pouring out My wrath on them in the wilderness to put an end to them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 14, 'But I acted because of My name, so that it would not be profaned in the eyes of the nations in whose sight I had brought them out.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 15, 'However, I swore to them in the wilderness that I would not bring them into the land I had given [them]-- the most beautiful of all lands, flowing with milk and honey--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 16, 'because they rejected My ordinances, profaned My Sabbaths, and did not follow My statutes. For their hearts went after their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 17, 'But I spared them from destruction and did not bring them to an end in the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 18, '"Then I said to their children in the wilderness: Don''t follow the statutes of your fathers, defile yourselves with their idols, or keep their ordinances.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 19, 'I am the LORD your God. Follow My statutes, keep My ordinances, and practice them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 20, 'Keep My Sabbaths holy, and they will be a sign between Me and you, so you may know that I am the LORD your God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 21, '"But the children rebelled against Me. They did not follow My statutes or carefully keep My ordinances-- the person who does them will live by them. They also profaned My Sabbaths. So I considered pouring out My wrath on them and exhausting My anger against them in the wilderness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 22, 'But I withheld My hand and acted because of My name, so that it would not be profaned in the eyes of the nations in whose sight I brought them out.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 23, 'However, I swore to them in the wilderness that I would disperse them among the nations and scatter them among the countries.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 24, 'For they did not practice My ordinances but rejected My statutes and profaned My Sabbaths, and their eyes were fixed on their fathers'' idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 25, 'I also gave them statutes that were not good and ordinances that did not bring them life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 26, 'When they made every firstborn pass through [the fire], I defiled them through their gifts in order to devastate them so they would know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 27, '"Therefore, son of man, speak to the house of Israel, and tell them: This is what the Lord God says: In this way also your fathers blasphemed Me by committing treachery against Me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 28, 'When I brought them into the land that I swore to give them and they saw any high hill or leafy tree, they offered their sacrifices and presented their offensive offerings there. They also sent up their pleasing aromas and poured out their drink offerings there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 29, 'So I asked them: What is this high place you are going to? And it is called High Place to this day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 30, '"Therefore say to the house of Israel: This is what the Lord God says: Are you defiling yourselves the way your fathers did, and prostituting yourselves with their detestable things?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 31, 'When you offer your gifts, making your children pass through the fire, you continue to defile yourselves with all your idols to this day. So should I be consulted by you, house of Israel? As I live"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "I will not be consulted by you!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 32, '"When you say: Let us be like the nations, like the peoples of [other] countries, worshiping wood and stone, what you have in mind will never happen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 33, 'As I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "I will rule over you with a strong hand, an outstretched arm, and outpoured wrath.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 34, 'I will bring you from the peoples and gather you from the countries where you were scattered, with a strong hand, an outstretched arm, and outpoured wrath.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 35, 'I will lead you into the wilderness of the peoples and enter into judgment with you there face to face.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 36, 'Just as I entered into judgment with your fathers in the wilderness of the land of Egypt, so I will enter into judgment with you." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 37, '"I will make you pass under the rod and will bring you into the bond of the covenant.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 38, 'And I will also purge you of those who rebel and transgress against Me. I will bring them out of the land where they live as foreign residents, but they will not enter the land of Israel. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 39, '"As for you, house of Israel, this is what the Lord God says: Go and serve your idols, each of you. But afterwards you will surely listen to Me, and you will no longer defile My holy name with your gifts and idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 40, 'For on My holy mountain, Israel''s high mountain"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "there the entire house of Israel, all of them, will serve Me in the land. There I will accept them and will require your contributions and choicest gifts, all your holy offerings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 41, 'When I bring you from the peoples and gather you from the countries where you have been scattered, I will accept you as a pleasing aroma. And I will demonstrate My holiness through you in the sight of the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 42, 'When I lead you into the land of Israel, the land I swore to give your fathers, you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 43, 'There you will remember your ways and all your deeds you have defiled yourselves with, and you will loathe yourselves for all the evil things you have done.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 44, 'You will know that I am the LORD, house of Israel, when I have dealt with you because of My name rather than according to your evil ways and corrupt acts." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 45, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 46, '"Son of man, face the south and preach against it. Prophesy against the forest land in the Negev,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 47, 'and say to the forest there: Hear the word of the LORD! This is what the Lord God says: I am about to ignite a fire in you, and it will devour every green tree and every dry tree in you. The blazing flame will not be extinguished, and every face from the south to the north will be scorched by it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 48, 'Then all people will see that I, Yahweh, have kindled it. It will not be extinguished."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 20, 49, 'Then I said, "Ah, Lord God, they are saying of me: Isn''t he [just] posing riddles?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me again:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 2, '"Son of man, turn your face toward Jerusalem and preach against the sanctuaries. Prophesy against the land of Israel,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 3, 'and say to it: This is what the LORD says: I am against you. I will draw My sword from its sheath and cut off both the righteous and the wicked from you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 4, 'Since I will cut off [both] the righteous and the wicked, My sword will therefore come out of its sheath against everyone from the south to the north.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 5, 'So all the people will know that I, the LORD, have taken My sword from its sheath-- it will not be sheathed again.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 6, '"But you, son of man, groan! Groan bitterly with a broken heart right before their eyes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 7, 'And when they ask you: Why are you groaning? then say: Because of the news that is coming. Every heart will melt, and every hand will become weak. Every spirit will be discouraged, and every knee will turn to water. Yes, it is coming and it will happen." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 8, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 9, '"Son of man, prophesy: This is what the Lord says! You are to proclaim: A sword! A sword is sharpened and also polished.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 10, 'It is sharpened for slaughter, polished to flash like lightning! Should we rejoice? The scepter of My son, the sword despises every tree.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 11, 'The sword is given to be polished, to be grasped in the hand. It is sharpened, and it is polished, to be put in the hand of the slayer.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 12, 'Cry out and wail, son of man, for it is against My people. It is against all the princes of Israel! They are given over to the sword with My people. Therefore strike [your] thigh [in grief].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 13, 'Surely it will be a trial! And what if the sword despises even the scepter? The scepter will not continue. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 14, 'Therefore, son of man, prophesy and clap [your] hands together. Let the sword strike two times, even three. It is a sword for massacre, a sword for great massacre-- it surrounds them!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 15, 'I have appointed a sword for slaughter at all their gates, so that their hearts may melt and many may stumble. Alas! It is ready to flash like lightning; it is drawn for slaughter.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 16, 'Slash to the right; turn to the left-- wherever your blade is directed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 17, 'I also will clap My hands together, and I will satisfy My wrath. I, the LORD, have spoken."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 18, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 19, '"Now you, son of man, mark out two roads that the sword of Babylon''s king can take. Both of them should originate from the same land. And make a signpost at the fork in the road to [each] city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 20, 'Mark out a road that the sword can take to Rabbah of the Ammonites and to Judah into fortified Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 21, 'For the king of Babylon stands at the split in the road, at the fork of the two roads, to practice divination: he shakes the arrows, consults the idols, and observes the liver.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 22, 'The answer marked Jerusalem appears in his right hand, [indicating] that he should set up battering rams, give the order to slaughter, raise a battle cry, set battering rams against the gates, build a ramp, and construct a siege wall.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 23, 'It will seem like false divination in the eyes of those who have sworn an oath to the Babylonians, but it will draw attention to [their] guilt so that they will be captured.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 24, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: Because you have drawn attention to your guilt, exposing your transgressions, so that your sins are revealed in all your actions, since you have done this, you will be captured by them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 25, 'And you, profane and wicked prince of Israel, the day has come for your punishment."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 26, 'This is what the Lord God says: Remove the turban, and take off the crown. Things will not remain as they are; exalt the lowly and bring down the exalted.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 27, 'A ruin, a ruin, I will make it a ruin! Yet this will not happen until He comes; I have given the judgment to Him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 28, '"Now prophesy, son of man, and say: This is what the Lord God says concerning the Ammonites and their contempt. You are to proclaim: Sword, sword! [You are] drawn for slaughter, polished to consume, to flash like lightning.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 29, 'While they offer false visions and lying divinations about you, [the time] has come to put you to the necks of the profane wicked ones; the day has come for your punishment.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 30, 'Return [it] to its sheath! I will judge you in the place where you were created, in the land of your origin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 31, 'I will pour out My indignation on you; I will blow the fire of My fury on you. I will hand you over to brutal men, skilled at destruction.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 21, 32, 'You will be fuel for the fire. Your blood will be [spilled] in the land. You will not be remembered, for I, the LORD, have spoken."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 2, '"Now, son of man, will you pass judgment? Will you pass judgment against the city of blood? Then explain all her abominations to her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 3, 'You are to say: This is what the Lord God says: A city that sheds blood within her [walls] so that her time of judgment has come and who makes idols for herself so that she is defiled!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 4, 'You are guilty of the blood you have shed, and you are defiled from the idols you have made. You have brought your [judgment] days near and have come to your years [of punishment]. Therefore, I have made you a disgrace to the nations and a mockery to all the lands.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 5, 'Those who are near and those far away from you will mock you, you infamous one full of turmoil.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 6, '"Look, every prince of Israel within you has used his strength to shed blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 7, 'Father and mother are treated with contempt, and the foreign resident is exploited within you. The fatherless and widow are oppressed in you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 8, 'You despise My holy things and profane My Sabbaths.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 9, 'There are men within you who slander in order to shed blood. People who [live] in you eat at the mountain [shrines]; they commit immoral acts within you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 10, 'Men within you have sexual intercourse with [their] father''s wife, and violate women during their menstrual impurity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 11, 'One man within you commits an abomination with his neighbor''s wife; another wickedly defiles his daughter-in-law; and [yet] another violates his sister, his father''s daughter.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 12, 'People who [live] in you accept bribes in order to shed blood. You take interest and profit [on a loan] and brutally extort your neighbors. You have forgotten Me." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 13, '"Now look, I clap My hands together against the unjust gain you have made and against the blood shed among you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 14, 'Will your courage endure or your hands be strong in the days when I deal with you? I, the LORD, have spoken, and I will act.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 15, 'I will disperse you among the nations and scatter you among the countries; I will purge your uncleanness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 16, 'You will be profaned in the sight of the nations. Then you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 17, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 18, '"Son of man, the house of Israel has become dross to Me. All of them are copper, tin, iron, and lead inside the furnace; they are the dross of silver.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 19, 'Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: Because all of you have become dross, I am about to gather you into Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 20, 'Just as one gathers silver, copper, iron, lead, and tin into the furnace to blow fire on them and melt them, so I will gather [you] in My anger and wrath, put you [inside], and melt you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 21, 'Yes, I will gather you together and blow on you with the fire of My fury, and you will be melted within the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 22, 'As silver is melted inside a furnace, so you will be melted inside the city. Then you will know that I, the LORD, have poured out My wrath on you."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 23, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 24, '"Son of man, say to her: You are a land that has not been cleansed, that has not received rain in the day of indignation.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 25, 'The conspiracy of her prophets within her is like a roaring lion tearing [its] prey: they devour people, seize wealth and valuables, and multiply the widows within her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 26, 'Her priests do violence to My law and profane My holy things. They make no distinction between the holy and the common, and they do not explain the difference between the clean and the unclean. They disregard My Sabbaths, and I am profaned among them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 27, '"Her officials within her are like wolves tearing [their] prey, shedding blood, and destroying lives in order to get unjust gain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 28, 'Her prophets plaster with whitewash for them by seeing false visions and lying divinations, and they say: This is what the Lord God says, when the LORD has not spoken.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 29, 'The people of the land have practiced extortion and committed robbery. They have oppressed the poor and needy and unlawfully exploited the foreign resident.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 30, 'I searched for a man among them who would repair the wall and stand in the gap before Me on behalf of the land so that I might not destroy it, but I found no one.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 22, 31, 'So I have poured out My indignation on them and consumed them with the fire of My fury. I have brought their actions down on their own heads." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me again:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 2, '"Son of man, there were two women, daughters of the same mother,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 3, 'who acted like prostitutes in Egypt, behaving promiscuously in their youth. Their breasts were fondled there, and their virgin nipples caressed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 4, 'The older one was named Oholah, and her sister was Oholibah. They became Mine and gave birth to sons and daughters. As for their names, Oholah represents Samaria and Oholibah represents Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 5, '"Oholah acted like a prostitute even though she was Mine. She lusted after her lovers, the Assyrians: warriors');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 6, 'dressed in blue, governors and prefects, all of them desirable young men, horsemen riding on steeds.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 7, 'She offered her sexual favors to them; all of them were the elite of Assyria. She defiled herself with all those she lusted after and with all their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 8, 'She didn''t give up her promiscuity that began in Egypt, when men slept with her in her youth, caressed her virgin nipples, and poured out their lust on her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 9, 'Therefore, I handed her over to her lovers, the Assyrians she lusted for.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 10, 'They exposed her nakedness, seized her sons and daughters, and killed her with the sword. Since they executed judgment against her, she became notorious among women.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 11, '"Now her sister Oholibah saw [this], but she was [even] more depraved in her lust than Oholah, and made her promiscuous acts worse than those of her sister.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 12, 'She lusted after the Assyrians: governors and prefects, warriors splendidly dressed, horsemen riding on steeds, all of them desirable young men.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 13, 'And I saw that she had defiled herself; both of them [had taken] the same path.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 14, 'But she increased her promiscuity when she saw male figures carved on the wall, images of the Chaldeans, engraved in vermilion,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 15, 'wearing belts on their waists and flowing turbans on their heads; all of them looked like officers, a depiction of the Babylonians in Chaldea, the land of their birth.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 16, 'At the sight of them she lusted after them and sent messengers to them in Chaldea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 17, 'Then the Babylonians came to her, to the bed of love, and defiled her with their lust. But after she was defiled by them, she turned away from them in disgust.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 18, 'When she flaunted her promiscuity and exposed her nakedness, I turned away from her in disgust just as I turned away from her sister.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 19, 'Yet she multiplied her acts of promiscuity, remembering the days of her youth when she acted like a prostitute in the land of Egypt');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 20, 'and lusted after their lovers, whose sexual members were like those of donkeys and whose emission was like that of stallions.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 21, 'So you revisited the indecency of your youth, when the Egyptians caressed your nipples to enjoy your youthful breasts.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 22, '"Therefore Oholibah, this is what the Lord God says: I am going to incite your lovers against you, those you turned away from in disgust. I will bring them against you from every side:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 23, 'the Babylonians and all the Chaldeans; Pekod, Shoa, and Koa; and all the Assyrians with them-- desirable young men, all of them governors and prefects, officers and administrators, all of them riding on horses.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 24, 'They will come against you with an alliance of nations and with weapons, chariots, and wagons. They will set themselves against you on every side with shields, bucklers, and helmets. I will delegate judgment to them, and they will judge you by their own standards.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 25, 'When I vent My jealous rage on you, they will deal with you in wrath. They will cut off your nose and ears, and your descendants will fall by the sword. They will seize your sons and daughters, and your descendants will be consumed by fire.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 26, 'They will strip off your clothes and take your beautiful jewelry.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 27, 'So I will put an end to your indecency and sexual immorality, which began in the land of Egypt, and you will not look longingly at them or remember Egypt any more.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 28, '"For this is what the Lord God says: I am going to hand you over to those you hate, to those you turned away from in disgust.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 29, 'They will treat you with hatred, take all you have worked for, and leave you stark naked, so that the shame of your debauchery will be exposed, both your indecency and promiscuity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 30, 'These things will be done to you because you acted like a prostitute with the nations, defiling yourself with their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 31, 'You have followed the path of your sister, so I will put her cup in your hand."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 32, 'This is what the Lord God says: You will drink your sister''s cup, which is deep and wide. You will be an object of ridicule and scorn, for it holds [so] much.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 33, 'You will be filled with drunkenness and grief, with a cup of devastation and desolation, the cup of your sister Samaria.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 34, 'You will drink it and drain [it]; then you will gnaw its broken pieces, and tear your breasts. For I have spoken. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 35, 'Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: "Because you have forgotten Me and cast Me behind your back, you must bear the consequences of your indecency and promiscuity."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 36, 'Then the LORD said to me: "Son of man, will you pass judgment against Oholah and Oholibah? Then declare their abominations to them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 37, 'For they have committed adultery, and blood is on their hands; they have committed adultery with their idols. They have even made the children they bore to Me pass through [the fire] as food for the idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 38, 'They also did this to Me: they defiled My sanctuary on that same day and profaned My Sabbaths.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 39, 'On the same day they slaughtered their children for their idols, they entered My sanctuary to profane it. Yes, that is what they did inside My house.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 40, '"In addition, they sent for men who came from far away when a messenger was dispatched to them. And look how they came! You bathed, painted your eyes, and adorned yourself with jewelry for them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 41, 'You sat on a luxurious couch with a table spread before it, on which you had set My incense and oil.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 42, 'The sound of a carefree crowd was there. Drunkards from the desert were brought in, along with common men. They put bracelets on the women''s hands and beautiful crowns on their heads.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 43, 'Then I said concerning this woman worn out by adultery: Will they now have illicit sex with her, even her?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 44, 'Yet they had sex with her as one does with a prostitute. This is how they had sex with Oholah and Oholibah, those obscene women.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 45, 'But righteous men will judge them the way adulteresses and those who shed blood are judged, for they are adulteresses and blood is on their hands.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 46, '"This is what the Lord God says: Summon an assembly against them and consign them to terror and plunder.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 47, 'The assembly will stone them and cut them down with their swords. They will kill their sons and daughters and burn their houses with fire.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 48, 'So I will put an end to indecency in the land, and all the women will be admonished not to imitate your indecent behavior.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 23, 49, 'They will repay you for your indecency, and you will bear the consequences for your sins of idolatry. Then you will know that I am the Lord God."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me in the ninth year, in the tenth month, on the tenth [day] of the month:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 2, '"Son of man, write down today''s date, this very day. The king of Babylon has laid siege to Jerusalem this very day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 3, 'Now speak a parable to the rebellious house. Tell them: This is what the Lord God says: Put the pot on [the fire]-- put [it] on, and then pour water into it!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 4, 'Place the pieces of meat in it, every good piece-- thigh and shoulder. Fill it with choice bones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 5, 'Take the choicest of the flock and also pile up the fuel under it. Bring it to a boil and cook the bones in it."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 6, 'Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: Woe to the city of bloodshed, the pot that has rust inside it, and whose rust will not come off! Empty it piece by piece; lots should not be cast for its contents.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 7, 'For the blood she shed is in her midst. She put it out on the bare rock; she didn''t pour it on the ground to cover it with dust.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 8, 'In order to stir up wrath and take vengeance, I have put her blood on the bare rock, so that it would not be covered.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 9, 'Therefore, this is what the Lord God says: Woe to the city of bloodshed! I Myself will make the pile of kindling large.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 10, 'Pile on the logs and kindle the fire! Cook the meat well and mix in the spices! Let the bones be burned!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 11, 'Set the empty pot on its coals so that it becomes hot and its copper glows. Then its impurity will melt inside it; its rust will be consumed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 12, 'It has frustrated every effort; its thick rust will not come off. Into the fire with its rust!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 13, 'Because of the indecency of your uncleanness-- since I tried to purify you, but you would not be purified from your uncleanness-- you will not be pure again until I have satisfied My wrath on you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 14, 'I, the LORD, have spoken. It is coming, and I will do it! I will not refrain, I will not show pity, and I will not relent. I will judge you according to your ways and deeds. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 15, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 16, '"Son of man, I am about to take the delight of your eyes away from you with a fatal blow. But you must not lament or weep or let your tears flow.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 17, 'Groan quietly; do not observe mourning rites for the dead. Put on your turban and strap your sandals on your feet; do not cover [your] mustache or eat the bread of mourners."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 18, 'I spoke to the people in the morning, and my wife died in the evening. The next morning I did just as I was commanded.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 19, 'Then the people asked me, "Won''t you tell us what these things you are doing mean for us?"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 20, 'So I answered them: "The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 21, '''Say to the house of Israel: This is what the Lord God says: I am about to desecrate My sanctuary, the pride of your power, the delight of your eyes, and the desire of your heart. Also, the sons and daughters you left behind will fall by the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 22, 'Then you will do just as I have done: You will not cover [your] mustache or eat the bread of mourners.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 23, 'Your turbans will remain on your heads and your sandals on your feet. You will not lament or weep but will waste away because of your sins and will groan to one another.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 24, 'Now Ezekiel will be a sign for you. You will do everything that he has done. When this happens, you will know that I am the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 25, '" ''Son of man, know that on the day I take their stronghold from them, their pride and joy, the delight of their eyes and the longing of their hearts, [as well as] their sons and daughters,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 26, 'on that day a fugitive will come to you and report the news.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 24, 27, 'On that day your mouth will be opened [to talk] with him; you will speak and no longer be mute. So you will be a sign for them, and they will know that I am the LORD.''"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 1, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 2, '"Son of man, turn your face toward the Ammonites and prophesy against them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 3, 'Say to the Ammonites: Hear the word of the Lord God: This is what the Lord God says: Because you said: Good! about My sanctuary when it was desecrated, about the land of Israel when it was laid waste, and about the house of Judah when they went into exile,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 4, 'therefore I am about to give you to the people of the east as a possession. They will set up their encampments and pitch their tents among you. They will eat your fruit and drink your milk.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 5, 'I will make Rabbah a pasture for camels and Ammon a sheepfold. Then you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 6, 'For this is what the Lord God says: "Because you clapped [your] hands, stamped [your] feet, and rejoiced over the land of Israel with wholehearted contempt,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 7, 'therefore I am about to stretch out My hand against you and give you as plunder to the nations. I will cut you off from the peoples and eliminate you from the countries. I will destroy you, and you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 8, 'This is what the Lord God says: "Because Moab and Seir said: Look, the house of Judah is like all the [other] nations,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 9, 'therefore I am about to expose Moab''s flank beginning with its frontier cities, the pride of the land: Beth-jeshimoth, Baal-meon, and Kiriathaim.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 10, 'I will give it along with Ammon to the people of the east as a possession, so that Ammon will not be remembered among the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 11, 'So I will execute judgments against Moab, and they will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 12, 'This is what the Lord God says: "Because Edom acted vengefully against the house of Judah and incurred grievous guilt by taking revenge on them,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 13, 'therefore this is what the Lord God says: I will stretch out My hand against Edom and cut off both man and animal from it. I will make it a wasteland; they will fall by the sword from Teman to Dedan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 14, 'I will take My vengeance on Edom through My people Israel, and they will deal with Edom according to My anger and wrath. So they will know My vengeance." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 15, 'This is what the Lord God says: "Because the Philistines acted in vengeance and took revenge with deep contempt, destroying [because of their] ancient hatred,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 16, 'therefore this is what the Lord God says: I am about to stretch out My hand against the Philistines, cutting off the Cherethites and wiping out what remains of the coastal peoples.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 25, 17, 'I will execute great vengeance against them with furious rebukes. They will know that I am the LORD when I take My vengeance on them."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 1, 'In the eleventh year, on the first [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 2, '"Son of man, because Tyre said about Jerusalem: Good! The gateway to the peoples is shattered. She has been turned over to me. I will be filled [now that] she lies in ruins,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 3, 'therefore this is what the Lord God says: See, I am against you, Tyre! I will raise up many nations against you, just as the sea raises its waves.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 4, 'They will destroy the walls of Tyre and demolish her towers. I will scrape the soil from her and turn her into a bare rock.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 5, 'She will become a place in the sea to spread nets, for I have spoken." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God. "She will become plunder for the nations,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 6, 'and her villages on the mainland will be slaughtered by the sword. Then they will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 7, 'For this is what the Lord God says: "See, I am about to bring King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon, king of kings, against Tyre from the north with horses, chariots, cavalry, and a vast company of troops.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 8, 'He will slaughter your villages on the mainland with the sword. He will set up siege works against you, and will build a ramp and raise a wall of shields against you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 9, 'He will direct the blows of his battering rams against your walls and tear down your towers with his iron tools.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 10, 'His horses will be so numerous that their dust will cover you. When he enters your gates as [an army] entering a breached city, your walls will shake from the noise of cavalry, wagons, and chariots.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 11, 'He will trample all your streets with the hooves of his horses. He will slaughter your people with the sword, and your mighty pillars will fall to the ground.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 12, 'They will take your wealth as spoil and plunder your merchandise. They will also demolish your walls and tear down your beautiful homes. Then they will throw your stones, timber, and soil into the water.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 13, 'I will put an end to the noise of your songs, and the sound of your lyres will no longer be heard.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 14, 'I will turn you into a bare rock, and you will be a place to spread nets. You will never be rebuilt, for I, the LORD, have spoken." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 15, 'This is what the Lord God says to Tyre: "Won''t the coasts and islands quake at the sound of your downfall, when the wounded groan and slaughter occurs within you?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 16, 'All the princes of the sea will descend from their thrones, remove their robes, and strip off their embroidered garments. They will clothe themselves with trembling; they will sit on the ground, tremble continually, and be appalled at you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 17, 'Then they will lament for you and say of you: How you have perished, city of renown, you who were populated from the seas! She who was powerful on the sea, she and all of her inhabitants inflicted their terror.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 18, 'Now the coastlands tremble on the day of your downfall; the islands in the sea are alarmed by your demise."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 19, 'For this is what the Lord God says: "When I make you a ruined city like [other] deserted cities, when I raise up the deep against you so that the mighty waters cover you,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 20, 'then I will bring you down [to be] with those who descend to the Pit, to the people of antiquity. I will make you dwell in the underworld like the ancient ruins, with those who descend to the Pit, so that you will no longer be inhabited or display [your] splendor in the land of the living.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 26, 21, 'I will make you an object of horror, and you will no longer exist. You will be sought but will never be found again." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 2, '"Now, son of man, lament for Tyre.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 3, 'Say to Tyre, who is located at the entrance of the sea, merchant of the peoples to many coasts and islands: This is what the Lord God says: Tyre, you declared: I am perfect in beauty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 4, 'Your realm was in the heart of the sea; your builders perfected your beauty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 5, 'They constructed all your planking with pine trees from Senir. They took a cedar from Lebanon to make a mast for you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 6, 'They made your oars of oaks from Bashan. They made your deck of cypress wood from the coasts of Cyprus, [inlaid] with ivory.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 7, 'Your sail was [made of] fine embroidered linen from Egypt, and served as your banner. Your awning was of blue and purple fabric from the coasts of Elishah.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 8, 'The inhabitants of Sidon and Arvad were your rowers. Your wise men were within you, Tyre; they were your helmsmen.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 9, 'The elders of Gebal and its wise men were within you, repairing your leaks. All the ships of the sea and their sailors came to you to barter for your goods.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 10, '[Men of] Persia, Lud, and Put were in your army, [serving] as your warriors. They hung shields and helmets in you; they gave you splendor.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 11, 'Men of Arvad and Helech were [stationed] on your walls all around, and Gamadites were in your towers. They hung their shields all around your walls; they perfected your beauty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 12, '"Tarshish was your trading partner because of [your] great wealth of every kind. They exchanged silver, iron, tin, and lead for your merchandise.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 13, 'Javan, Tubal, and Meshech were your merchants. They exchanged slaves and bronze utensils for your goods.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 14, 'Those from Beth-togarmah exchanged horses, war horses, and mules for your merchandise.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 15, 'Men of Dedanwere also your merchants; many coasts and islands were your regular markets. They brought back ivory tusks and ebony as your payment.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 16, 'Aramwas your trading partner because of your numerous products. They exchanged turquoise, purple and embroidered cloth, fine linen, coral, and rubies for your merchandise.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 17, 'Judah and the land of Israel were your merchants. They exchanged wheat from Minnith, meal, honey, oil, and balm for your goods.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 18, 'Damascus was also your trading partner because of your numerous products and your great wealth of every kind, [trading] in wine from Helbon and white wool.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 19, 'Vedan and Javan from Uzaldealt in your merchandise; wrought iron, cassia, and aromatic cane were [exchanged] for your goods.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 20, 'Dedan was your merchant in saddlecloths for riding.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 21, 'Arabia and all the princes of Kedar were your business partners, trading with you in lambs, rams, and goats.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 22, 'The merchants of Sheba and Raamah traded with you. They exchanged gold, the best of all spices, and all kinds of precious stones for your merchandise.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 23, 'Haran, Canneh, Eden, the merchants of Sheba, Asshur, and Chilmad traded with you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 24, 'They were your merchants in choice garments, cloaks of blue and embroidered materials, and multicolored carpets, which were bound and secured with cords in your marketplace.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 25, 'Ships of Tarshish were the carriers for your goods. So you became full and heavily loaded in the heart of the sea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 26, 'Your rowers have brought you onto the high seas, but the east wind has shattered you in the heart of the sea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 27, 'Your wealth, merchandise, and goods, your sailors and helmsmen, those who repair your leaks, those who barter for your goods, and all the warriors within you, with all the other people on board, sink into the heart of the sea on the day of your downfall.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 28, 'The countryside shakes at the sound of your sailors'' cries.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 29, 'All those who handle an oar disembark from their ships. The sailors and all the helmsmen of the sea stand on the shore.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 30, 'They raise their voices over you and cry out bitterly. They throw dust on their heads; they roll in ashes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 31, 'They shave their heads because of you and wrap themselves in sackcloth. They weep over you with deep anguish and bitter mourning.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 32, 'In their wailing they lament for you, mourning over you: Who was like Tyre, silenced in the middle of the sea?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 33, 'When your merchandise was unloaded from the seas, you satisfied many peoples. You enriched the kings of the earth with your abundant wealth and goods.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 34, 'Now you are shattered by the sea in the depths of the waters; your goods and the people within you have gone down.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 35, 'All the inhabitants of the coasts and islands are appalled at you. Their kings shudder with fear; [their] faces are contorted.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 27, 36, 'Those who trade among the peoples hiss at you; you have become an object of horror and will never exist again."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 2, '"Son of man, say to the ruler of Tyre: This is what the Lord God says: Your heart is proud, and you have said: I am a god; I sit in the seat of gods in the heart of the sea. Yet you are a man and not a god, though you have regarded your heart as that of a god.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 3, 'Yes, you are wiser than Daniel; no secret is hidden from you!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 4, 'By your wisdom and understanding you have acquired wealth for yourself. You have acquired gold and silver for your treasuries.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 5, 'By your great skill in trading you have increased your wealth, but your heart has become proud because of your wealth."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 6, 'Therefore this is what the Lord God says: Because you regard your heart as that of a god,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 7, 'I am about to bring strangers against you, ruthless men from the nations. They will draw their swords against your magnificent wisdom and will defile your splendor.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 8, 'They will bring you down to the Pit, and you will die a violent death in the heart of the sea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 9, 'Will you still say: I am a god, in the presence of those who kill you? Yet you will be [shown to be] a man, not a god, in the hands of those who kill you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 10, 'You will die the death of the uncircumcised at the hands of strangers. For I have spoken. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 11, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 12, '"Son of man, lament for the king of Tyre and say to him: This is what the Lord God says: You were the seal of perfection, full of wisdom and perfect in beauty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 13, 'You were in Eden, the garden of God. Every kind of precious stone covered you: carnelian, topaz, and diamond, beryl, onyx, and jasper, sapphire, turquoise and emerald. Your mountings and settings were crafted in gold; they were prepared on the day you were created.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 14, 'You were an anointed guardian cherub, for I had appointed you. You were on the holy mountain of God; you walked among the fiery stones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 15, 'From the day you were created you were blameless in your ways until wickedness was found in you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 16, 'Through the abundance of your trade, you were filled with violence, and you sinned. So I expelled you in disgrace from the mountain of God, and banished you, guardian cherub, from among the fiery stones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 17, 'Your heart became proud because of your beauty; For the sake of your splendor you corrupted your wisdom. So I threw you down to the earth; I made a spectacle of you before kings.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 18, 'You profaned your sanctuaries by the magnitude of your iniquities in your dishonest trade. So I sent out fire from within you, and it consumed you. I reduced you to ashes on the ground in the sight of everyone watching you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 19, 'All those who know you among the nations are appalled at you. You have become an object of horror and will never exist again."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 20, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 21, '"Son of man, turn your face toward Sidon and prophesy against it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 22, 'You are to say: This is what the Lord God says: Look! I am against you, Sidon, and I will display My glory within you. They will know that I am the LORD when I execute judgments against her and demonstrate My holiness through her.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 23, 'I will send a plague against her and bloodshed in her streets; the slain will fall within her, while the sword is against her on every side. Then they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 24, '"The house of Israel will no longer be hurt by prickling briers or painful thorns from all their neighbors who treat them with contempt. Then they will know that I am the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 25, '"This is what the Lord God says: When I gather the house of Israel from the peoples where they are scattered and demonstrate My holiness through them in the sight of the nations, then they will live in their own land, which I gave to My servant Jacob.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 28, 26, 'They will live there securely, build houses, and plant vineyards. They will live securely when I execute judgments against all their neighbors who treat them with contempt. Then they will know that I am the LORD their God."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 1, 'In the tenth year, in the tenth [month] on the twelfth [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 2, '"Son of man, turn your face toward Pharaoh king of Egypt and prophesy against him and against all of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 3, 'Speak [to him] and say: This is what the Lord God says: Look, I am against you, Pharaoh king of Egypt, the great monsterlying in the middle of his Nile, who says: My Nile is my own; I made [it] for myself.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 4, 'I will put hooks in your jaws and make the fish of your streams cling to your scales. I will haul you up from the middle of your Nile, and all the fish of your streams will cling to your scales.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 5, 'I will leave you in the desert, you and all the fish of your streams. You will fall on the open ground and will not be taken away or gathered [for burial]. I have given you to the beasts of the earth and the birds of the sky as food.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 6, 'Then all the inhabitants of Egypt will know that I am the LORD, for they have been a staff [made] of reed to the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 7, 'When Israel grasped you by the hand, you splintered, tearing all their shoulders; when they leaned on you, you shattered and made all their hips unsteady.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 8, '"Therefore this is what the Lord God says: I am going to bring a sword against you and wipe out man and animal from you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 9, 'The land of Egypt will be a desolate ruin. Then they will know that I am the LORD. Because you said: The Nile is my own; I made [it],');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 10, 'therefore, I am against you and your Nile. I will turn the land of Egypt into ruins, a desolate waste from Migdol to Syene, as far as the border of Cush.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 11, 'No human foot will pass through it, and no animal foot will pass through it. It will be uninhabited for 40 years.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 12, 'I will make the land of Egypt a desolation among desolate lands, and its cities will be a desolation among ruined cities for 40 years. I will disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them across the countries.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 13, '"For this is what the Lord God says: At the end of 40 years I will gather the Egyptians from the nations where they were dispersed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 14, 'I will restore the fortunes of Egypt and bring them back to the land of Pathros, the land of their origin. There they will be a lowly kingdom.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 15, 'Egypt will be the lowliest of kingdoms and will never again exalt itself over the nations. I will make them so small they cannot rule over the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 16, 'It will never again be an object of trust for the house of Israel, drawing attention to their sin of turning to the Egyptians. Then they will know that I am the Lord God."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 17, 'In the twenty-seventh year in the first [month], on the first [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 18, '"Son of man, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon made his army labor strenuously against Tyre. Every head was made bald and every shoulder chafed, but he and his army received no compensation from Tyre for the labor he expended against it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 19, 'Therefore this is what the Lord God says: I am going to give the land of Egypt to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, who will carry off its wealth, seizing its spoil and taking its plunder. This will be his army''s compensation.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 20, 'I have given him the land of Egypt as the pay he labored for, since they worked for Me." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 29, 21, '"In that day I will cause a horn to sprout for the house of Israel, and I will enable you to speak out among them. Then they will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 2, '"Son of man, prophesy and say: This is what the Lord God says: Wail: Alas for the day!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 3, 'For a day is near; a day belonging to the LORD is near. It will be a day of clouds, a time [of doom] for the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 4, 'A sword will come against Egypt, and there will be anguish in Cush when the slain fall in Egypt, and its wealth is taken away, and its foundations are torn down.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 5, 'Cush, Put, and Lud, and all the various foreign troops, plus Libya and the men of the covenant land will fall by the sword along with them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 6, 'This is what the LORD says: Those who support Egypt will fall, and its proud strength will collapse. From Migdol to Syene they will fall within it by the sword. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 7, 'They will be desolate among desolate lands, and their cities will lie among ruined cities.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 8, 'They will know that I am the LORD when I set fire to Egypt and all its allies are shattered.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 9, 'On that day, messengers will go out from Me in ships to terrify confident Cush. Anguish will come over them on the day of Egypt''s [doom]. For indeed it is coming."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 10, 'This is what the Lord God says: I will put an end to the hordes of Egypt by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 11, 'He along with his people, ruthless men from the nations, will be brought in to destroy the land. They will draw their swords against Egypt and fill the land with the slain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 12, 'I will make the streams dry and sell the land into the hands of evil men. I will bring desolation on the land and everything in it by the hands of foreigners. I, the LORD, have spoken.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 13, 'This is what the Lord God says: I will destroy the idols and put an end to the false gods in Memphis. There will no longer be a prince from the land of Egypt. So I will instill fear in that land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 14, 'I will make Pathros desolate, set fire to Zoan, and execute judgments on Thebes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 15, 'I will pour out My wrath on Pelusium, the stronghold of Egypt, and will wipe out the crowds of Thebes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 16, 'I will set fire to Egypt; Pelusium will writhe in anguish, Thebes will be breached, and Memphis will face foes in broad daylight.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 17, 'The young men of On and Pi-beseth will fall by the sword, and those cities will go into captivity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 18, 'The day will be dark in Tehaphnehes, when I break the yoke of Egypt there and its proud strength comes to an end in the city. A cloud will cover Tehaphnehes, and its villages will go into captivity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 19, 'So I will execute judgments against Egypt, and they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 20, 'In the eleventh year, in the first [month], on the seventh [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 21, '"Son of man, I have broken the arm of Pharaoh king of Egypt. Look, it has not been bandaged-- [no] medicine has been applied and no splint put on to bandage it so that it can grow strong [enough] to handle a sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 22, 'Therefore this is what the Lord God says: Look! I am against Pharaoh king of Egypt. I will break his arms, both the strong one and the one [already] broken, and will make the sword fall from his hand.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 23, 'I will disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them among the countries.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 24, 'I will strengthen the arms of Babylon''s king and place My sword in his hand. But I will break the arms of Pharaoh, and he will groan before him as a mortally wounded man.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 25, 'I will strengthen the arms of Babylon''s king, but Pharaoh''s arms will fall. They will know that I am the LORD when I place My sword in the hand of Babylon''s king and he wields it against the land of Egypt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 30, 26, 'When I disperse the Egyptians among the nations and scatter them among the countries, they will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 1, 'In the eleventh year, in the third [month], on the first [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 2, '"Son of man, say to Pharaoh king of Egypt and to his hordes: Who are you like in your greatness?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 3, 'Think of Assyria, a cedar in Lebanon, with beautiful branches and shady foliage, and of lofty height. Its top was among the clouds.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 4, 'The waters caused it to grow; the underground springs made it tall, directing their rivers all around the place where the tree was planted and sending their channels to all the trees of the field.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 5, 'Therefore the cedar became greater in height than all the trees of the field. Its branches multiplied, and its boughs grew long as it spread [them] out because of the plentiful water.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 6, 'All the birds of the sky nested in its branches, and all the animals of the field gave birth beneath its boughs; all the great nations lived in its shade.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 7, 'It was beautiful in its greatness, in the length of its limbs, for its roots extended to abundant water.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 8, 'The cedars in God''s garden could not rival it; the pine trees couldn''t compare with its branches, nor could the plane trees match its boughs. No tree in the garden of God could compare with it in beauty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 9, 'I made it beautiful with its many limbs, and all the trees of Eden, which were in God''s garden, envied it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 10, '"Therefore this is what the Lord God says: Since it became great in height and set its top among the clouds, and it grew proud on account of its height,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 11, 'I determined to hand it over to a ruler of nations; he would surely deal with it. I banished it because of its wickedness.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 12, 'Foreigners, ruthless men from the nations, cut it down and left it lying. Its limbs fell on the mountains and in every valley; its boughs lay broken in all the earth''s ravines. All the peoples of the earth left its shade and abandoned it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 13, 'All the birds of the sky nested on its fallen trunk, and all the animals of the field were among its boughs.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 14, '[This happened] so that no trees [planted] beside water would become great in height and set their tops among the clouds, and so that no [other] well-watered trees would reach them in height. For they have all been consigned to death, to the underworld, among the people who descend to the Pit.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 15, '"This is what the Lord God says: I caused grieving on the day the cedar went down to Sheol. I closed off the underground deep because of it: I held back the rivers of the deep, and [its] abundant waters were restrained. I made Lebanon mourn on account of it, and all the trees of the field fainted because of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 16, 'I made the nations quake at the sound of its downfall, when I threw it down to Sheol [to be] with those who descend to the Pit. Then all the trees of Eden, all the well-watered trees, the choice and best of Lebanon, were comforted in the underworld.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 17, 'They too descended with it to Sheol, to those slain by the sword. As its alliesthey had lived in its shade among the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 31, 18, '"Who then are you like in glory and greatness among Eden''s trees? You also will be brought down to the underworld [to be] with the trees of Eden. You will lie among the uncircumcised with those slain by the sword. This is Pharaoh and all his hordes"-- the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 1, 'In the twelfth year, in the twelfth month, on the first [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 2, '"Son of man, lament for Pharaoh king of Egypt and say to him: You compare yourself to a lion of the nations, but you are like a monster in the seas. You thrash about in your rivers, churn up the waters with your feet, and muddy the rivers."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 3, 'This is what the Lord God says: I will spread My net over you with an assembly of many peoples, and they will haul you up in My net.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 4, 'I will abandon you on the land and hurl you on the open field. I will cause all the birds of the sky to settle on you and let the beasts of the entire earth eat their fill of you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 5, 'I will put your flesh on the mountains and fill the valleys with your carcass.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 6, 'I will drench the land with the flow of your blood, [even] to the mountains; the ravines will be filled with your [gore].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 7, 'When I snuff you out, I will cover the heavens and darken their stars. I will cover the sun with a cloud, and the moon will not give its light.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 8, 'I will darken all the shining lights in the heavens over you, and will bring darkness on your land. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 9, 'I will trouble the hearts of many peoples, when I bring about your destruction among the nations, in countries you do not know.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 10, 'I will cause many nations to be appalled at you, and their kings will shudder with fear because of you when I brandish My sword in front of them. On the day of your downfall each of them will tremble every moment for his life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 11, 'For this is what the Lord God says: The sword of Babylon''s king will come against you!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 12, 'I will make your hordes fall by the swords of warriors, all of them ruthless men from the nations. They will ravage Egypt''s pride, and all its hordes will be destroyed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 13, 'I will slaughter all its cattle that are beside many waters. No human foot will churn them again, and no cattle hooves will disturb them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 14, 'Then I will let their waters settle and will make their rivers flow like oil. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 15, 'When I make the land of Egypt a desolation, so that it is emptied of everything in it, when I strike down all who live there, then they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 16, '"This is a lament that will be chanted; the women of the nations will chant it. They will chant it over Egypt and all its hordes." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 17, 'In the twelfth year, on the fifteenth [day] of the month, the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 18, '"Son of man, wail over the hordes of Egypt and bring Egypt and the daughters of mighty nations down to the underworld, [to be] with those who descend to the Pit:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 19, 'Whom do you surpass in loveliness? Go down and be laid to rest with the uncircumcised!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 20, 'They will fall among those slain by the sword. A sword is appointed! They drag her and all her hordes away.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 21, 'Warrior leaders will speak from the middle of Sheol about him and his allies: They have come down; the uncircumcised lie slain by the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 22, 'Assyria is there with all her company; her graves are all around her. All of them are slain, fallen by the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 23, 'Her graves are set in the deepest regions of the Pit, and her company is all around her burial place. All of them are slain, fallen by the sword-- they who [once] spread terror in the land of the living.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 24, 'Elam is there with all her hordes around her grave. All of them are slain, fallen by the sword-- they who went down to the underworld uncircumcised, who [once] spread their terror in the land of the living. They bear their disgrace with those who descend to the Pit.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 25, 'Among the slain they prepare a resting place for Elam with all her hordes. Her graves are all around her. All of them are uncircumcised, slain by the sword, although their terror was [once] spread in the land of the living. They bear their disgrace with those who descend to the Pit. They are placed among the slain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 26, 'Meshech and Tubalare there, with all their hordes. Their graves are all around them. All of them are uncircumcised, slain by the sword, although their terror was [once] spread in the land of the living.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 27, 'They do not lie down with the fallen warriors of the uncircumcised, who went down to Sheol with their weapons of war, whose swords were placed under their heads. The punishment for their sins rested on their bones, although the terror of [these] warriors was [once] in the land of the living.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 28, 'But you will be shattered and will lie down among the uncircumcised, with those slain by the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 29, 'Edom is there, her kings and all her princes, who, despite their strength, have been placed among those slain by the sword. They lie down with the uncircumcised, with those who descend to the Pit.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 30, 'All the leaders of the north and all the Sidonians are there. They went down in shame with the slain, despite the terror their strength inspired. They lie down uncircumcised with those slain by the sword. They bear their disgrace with those who descend to the Pit.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 31, 'Pharaoh will see them and be comforted over all his hordes-- Pharaoh and all his army, slain by the sword. [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 32, 32, 'For I will spread My terror in the land of the living, so Pharaoh and all his hordes will be laid to rest among the uncircumcised, with those slain by the sword." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 2, '"Son of man, speak to your people and tell them: Suppose I bring the sword against a land, and the people of that land select a man from among them, appointing him as their watchman,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 3, 'and he sees the sword coming against the land and blows his trumpet to warn the people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 4, 'Then, if anyone hears the sound of the trumpet but ignores the warning, and the sword comes and takes him away, his blood will be on his own head.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 5, '[Since] he heard the sound of the trumpet but ignored the warning, his blood is on his own hands. If he had taken warning, he would have saved his life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 6, 'However, if the watchman sees the sword coming but doesn''t blow the trumpet, so that the people aren''t warned, and the sword comes and takes away their lives, then they have been taken away because of their iniquity, but I will hold the watchman accountable for their blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 7, '"As for you, son of man, I have made you a watchman for the house of Israel. When you hear a word from My mouth, give them a warning from Me.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 8, 'If I say to the wicked: Wicked one, you will surely die, but you do not speak out to warn him about his way, that wicked person will die for his iniquity, yet I will hold you responsible for his blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 9, 'But if you warn a wicked person to turn from his way and he doesn''t turn from it, he will die for his iniquity, but you will have saved your life.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 10, '"Now as for you, son of man, say to the house of Israel: You have said this: Our transgressions and our sins are [heavy] on us, and we are wasting away because of them! How then can we survive?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 11, 'Tell them: As I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "I take no pleasure in the death of the wicked, but rather that the wicked person should turn from his way and live. Repent, repent of your evil ways! Why will you die, house of Israel?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 12, '"Now, son of man, say to your people: The righteousness of the righteous person will not save him on the day of his transgression; neither will the wickedness of the wicked person cause him to stumble on the day he turns from his wickedness. The righteous person won''t be able to survive by his righteousness on the day he sins.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 13, 'When I tell the righteous person that he will surely live, but he trusts in his righteousness and commits iniquity, then none of his righteousness will be remembered, and he will die because of the iniquity he has committed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 14, '"So when I tell the wicked person: You will surely die, but he repents of his sin and does what is just and right--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 15, 'he returns collateral, makes restitution for what he has stolen, and walks in the statutes of life without practicing iniquity-- he will certainly live; he will not die.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 16, 'None of the sins he committed will be held against him. He has done what is just and right; he will certainly live.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 17, '"But your people say: The Lord''s way isn''t fair, even though it is their own way that isn''t fair.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 18, 'When a righteous person turns from his righteousness and commits iniquity, he will die on account of this.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 19, 'But when a wicked person turns from his wickedness and does what is just and right, he will live because of this.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 20, 'Yet you say: The Lord''s way isn''t fair. I will judge each of you according to his ways, house of Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 21, 'In the twelfth year of our exile, in the tenth [month], on the fifth [day] of the month, a fugitive from Jerusalem came to me and reported, "The city has been taken!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 22, 'Now the hand of the LORD had been on me the evening before the fugitive arrived, and He opened my mouth before the man came to me in the morning. So my mouth was opened and I was no longer mute.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 23, 'Then the word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 24, '"Son of man, those who live in the ruins in the land of Israel are saying: Abraham was only one person, yet he received possession of the land. But we are many; the land has been given to us as a possession.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 25, 'Therefore say to them: This is what the Lord God says: You eat [meat] with blood [in it], raise your eyes to your idols, and shed blood. Should you then receive possession of the land?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 26, 'You have relied on your swords, you have committed abominations, and each of you has defiled his neighbor''s wife. Should you then receive possession of the land?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 27, '"Tell them this: This is what the Lord God says: As surely as I live, those who are in the ruins will fall by the sword, those in the open field I have given to wild animals to be devoured, and those in the strongholds and caves will die by plague.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 28, 'I will make the land a desolate waste, and its proud strength will come to an end. The mountains of Israel will become desolate, with no one passing through.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 29, 'They will know that I am the LORD when I make the land a desolate waste because of all the abominations they have committed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 30, '"Now, son of man, your people are talking about you near the [city] walls and in the doorways of their houses. One person speaks to another, each saying to his brother: Come and hear what the message is that comes from the LORD!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 31, 'So My people come to you in crowds, sit in front of you, and hear your words, but they don''t obey them. Although they express love with their mouths, their hearts pursue unjust gain.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 32, 'Yes, to them you are like a singer of love songs who has a beautiful voice and plays skillfully on an instrument. They hear your words, but they don''t obey them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 33, 33, 'Yet when it comes-- and it will definitely come-- then they will know that a prophet has been among them."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 2, '"Son of man, prophesy against the shepherds of Israel. Prophesy, and say to them: This is what the Lord God says to the shepherds: Woe to the shepherds of Israel, who have been feeding themselves! Shouldn''t the shepherds feed their flock?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 3, 'You eat the fat, wear the wool, and butcher the fatlings, but you do not tend the flock.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 4, 'You have not strengthened the weak, healed the sick, bandaged the injured, brought back the strays, or sought the lost. Instead, you have ruled them with violence and cruelty.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 5, 'They were scattered for lack of a shepherd; they became food for all the wild animals when they were scattered.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 6, 'My flock went astray on all the mountains and every high hill. They were scattered over the whole face of the earth, and there was no one searching or seeking [for them].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 7, '"Therefore, you shepherds, hear the word of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 8, 'As I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "because My flock has become [prey and] food for every wild animal since [they] lack a shepherd, for My shepherds do not search for My flock, and [because] the shepherds feed themselves rather than My flock,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 9, 'therefore, you shepherds, hear the word of the LORD!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 10, '"This is what the Lord God says: Look, I am against the shepherds. I will demand My flock from them and prevent them from shepherding the flock. The shepherds will no longer feed themselves, for I will rescue My flock from their mouths so that they will not be food for them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 11, '"For this is what the Lord God says: See, I Myself will search for My flock and look for them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 12, 'As a shepherd looks for his sheep on the day he is among his scattered flock, so I will look for My flock. I will rescue them from all the places where they have been scattered on a cloudy and dark day.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 13, 'I will bring them out from the peoples, gather them from the countries, and bring them into their own land. I will shepherd them on the mountains of Israel, in the ravines, and in all the inhabited places of the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 14, 'I will tend them with good pasture, and their grazing place will be on Israel''s lofty mountains. There they will lie down in a good grazing place; they will feed in rich pasture on the mountains of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 15, 'I will tend My flock and let them lie down." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 16, '"I will seek the lost, bring back the strays, bandage the injured, and strengthen the weak, but I will destroy the fat and the strong. I will shepherd them with justice.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 17, '"The Lord God says to you, My flock: I am going to judge between one sheep and another, between the rams and male goats.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 18, 'Isn''t it enough for you to feed on the good pasture? Must you also trample the rest of the pasture with your feet? Or [isn''t it enough] that you drink the clear water? Must you also muddy the rest with your feet?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 19, 'Yet My flock has to feed on what your feet have trampled, and drink what your feet have muddied.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 20, '"Therefore, this is what the Lord God says to them: See, I Myself will judge between the fat sheep and the lean sheep.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 21, 'Since you have pushed with flank and shoulder and butted all the weak ones with your horns until you scattered them all over,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 22, 'I will save My flock, and they will no longer be prey for you. I will judge between one sheep and another.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 23, 'I will appoint over them a single shepherd, My servant David, and he will shepherd them. He will tend them himself and will be their shepherd.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 24, 'I, the LORD, will be their God, and My servant David will be a prince among them. I, the LORD, have spoken.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 25, '"I will make a covenant of peace with them and eliminate dangerous animals in the land, so that they may live securely in the wilderness and sleep in the forest.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 26, 'I will make them and the area around My hill a blessing: I will send down showers in their season-- showers of blessing.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 27, 'The trees of the field will give their fruit, and the land will yield its produce; My flock will be secure in their land. They will know that I am the LORD when I break the bars of their yoke and rescue them from the hands of those who enslave them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 28, 'They will no longer be prey for the nations, and the wild animals of the land will not consume them. They will live securely, and no one will frighten [them].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 29, 'I will establish for them a place renowned for [its] agriculture, and they will no longer be victims of famine in the land. They will no longer endure the insults of the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 30, 'Then they will know that I, the LORD their God, am with them, and that they, the house of Israel, are My people." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 34, 31, '"You are My flock, the human flock of My pasture, and I am your God." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 2, '"Son of man, turn your face toward Mount Seir and prophesy against it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 3, 'Say to it: This is what the Lord God says: Look! I am against you, Mount Seir. I will stretch out My hand against you and make you a desolate waste.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 4, 'I will turn your cities into ruins, and you will become a desolation. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 5, '"Because you maintained an ancient hatred and handed over the Israelites to the power of the sword in the time of their disaster, the time of final punishment,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 6, 'therefore, as I live"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "I will destine you for bloodshed, and it will pursue you. Since you did not hate bloodshed, it will pursue you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 7, 'I will make Mount Seir a desolate waste and will cut off from it those who come and go.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 8, 'I will fill its mountains with the slain; those slain by the sword will fall on your hills, in your valleys, and in all your ravines.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 9, 'I will make you a perpetual desolation; your cities will not be inhabited. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 10, '"Because you said: These two nations and two lands will be mine, and we will possess them-- though the LORD was there--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 11, 'therefore, as I live"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "I will treat [you] according to the anger and jealousy you showed in your hatred of them. I will make Myself known among them when I judge you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 12, 'Then you will know that I, the LORD, have heard all the blasphemies you uttered against the mountains of Israel, saying: They are desolate. They have been given to us to devour!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 13, 'You boasted against Me with your mouth, and spoke many words against Me. I heard [it] Myself!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 14, '"This is what the Lord God says: While the whole world rejoices, I will make you a desolation.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 35, 15, 'Just as you rejoiced over the inheritance of the house of Israel because it became a desolation, so I will deal with you: you will become a desolation, Mount Seir, and [so will] all Edom in its entirety. Then they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 1, '"Son of man, prophesy to the mountains of Israel and say: Mountains of Israel, hear the word of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 2, 'This is what the Lord God says: Because the enemy has said about you, ''Good! The ancient heights have become our possession,''');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 3, 'therefore, prophesy and say: This is what the Lord God says: Because they have made you desolate and have trampled you from every side, so that you became a possession for the rest of the nations and an object of people''s gossip and slander,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 4, 'therefore, mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord God. This is what the Lord God says to the mountains and hills, to the ravines and valleys, to the desolate ruins and abandoned cities, which have become plunder and a mockery to the rest of the nations all around.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 5, '"This is what the Lord God says: Certainly in My burning zeal I speak against the rest of the nations and all of Edom, who took My land as their own possession with wholehearted rejoicing and utter contempt, so that its pastureland became plunder.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 6, 'Therefore, prophesy concerning the land of Israel and say to the mountains and hills, to the ravines and valleys: This is what the Lord God says: Look, I speak in My burning zeal because you have endured the insults of the nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 7, 'Therefore this is what the Lord God says: I swear that the nations all around you will endure their own insults.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 8, '"You, mountains of Israel, will put forth your branches and bear your fruit for My people Israel, since their arrival is near.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 9, 'Look! I am on your side; I will turn toward you, and you will be tilled and sown.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 10, 'I will fill you with people, with the whole house of Israel in its entirety. The cities will be inhabited and the ruins rebuilt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 11, 'I will fill you with people and animals, and they will increase and be fruitful. I will make you inhabited as you once were and make [you] better off than you were before. Then you will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 12, 'I will cause people, My people Israel, to walk on you; they will possess you, and you will be their inheritance. You will no longer deprive them of [their] children.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 13, '"This is what the Lord God says: Because people are saying to you: You devour men and deprive your nation of children,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 14, 'therefore, you will no longer devour men and deprive your nation of children." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 15, '"I will no longer allow the insults of the nations to be heard against you, and you will not have to endure the reproach of the peoples any more; you will no longer cause your nation to stumble." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 16, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 17, '"Son of man, while the house of Israel lived in their land, they defiled it with their conduct and actions. Their behavior before Me was like menstrual impurity.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 18, 'So I poured out My wrath on them because of the blood they had shed on the land, and because they had defiled it with their idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 19, 'I dispersed them among the nations, and they were scattered among the countries. I judged them according to their conduct and actions.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 20, 'When they came to the nations where they went, they profaned My holy name, because it was said about them: These are the people of the LORD, yet they had to leave His land [in exile].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 21, 'Then I had concern for My holy name, which the house of Israel profaned among the nations where they went.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 22, '"Therefore, say to the house of Israel: This is what the Lord God says: It is not for your sake that I will act, house of Israel, but for My holy name, which you profaned among the nations where you went.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 23, 'I will honor the holiness of My great name, which has been profaned among the nations-- the name you have profaned among them. The nations will know that I am Yahweh"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "when I demonstrate My holiness through you in their sight.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 24, '"For I will take you from the nations and gather you from all the countries, and will bring you into your own land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 25, 'I will also sprinkle clean water on you, and you will be clean. I will cleanse you from all your impurities and all your idols.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 26, 'I will give you a new heart and put a new spirit within you; I will remove your heart of stone and give you a heart of flesh.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 27, 'I will place My Spirit within you and cause you to follow My statutes and carefully observe My ordinances.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 28, 'Then you will live in the land that I gave your fathers; you will be My people, and I will be your God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 29, 'I will save you from all your uncleanness. I will summon the grain and make it plentiful, and will not bring famine on you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 30, 'I will also make the fruit of the trees and the produce of the field plentiful, so that you will no longer experience reproach among the nations on account of famine.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 31, '"Then you will remember your evil ways and your deeds that were not good, and you will loathe yourselves for your iniquities and abominations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 32, 'It is not for your sake that I will act"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "let this be known to you. Be ashamed and humiliated because of your ways, house of Israel!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 33, '"This is what the Lord God says: On the day I cleanse you from all your iniquities, I will cause the cities to be inhabited, and the ruins will be rebuilt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 34, 'The desolate land will be cultivated instead of lying desolate in the sight of everyone who passes by.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 35, 'Then they will say: This land that was desolate has become like the garden of Eden. The cities that were once ruined, desolate, and destroyed are [now] fortified and inhabited.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 36, 'Then the nations that remain around you will know that I, the LORD, have rebuilt what was destroyed and have replanted what was desolate. I, the LORD, have spoken and I will do [it].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 37, '"This is what the Lord God says: I will respond to the house of Israel and do this for them: I will multiply them in number like a flock.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 36, 38, 'So the ruined cities will be filled with a flock of people, just as the flock of sheep for sacrifice is filled in Jerusalem during its appointed festivals. Then they will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 1, 'The hand of the LORD was on me, and He brought me out by His Spirit and set me down in the middle of the valley; it was full of bones.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 2, 'He led me all around them. There were a great many of them on the surface of the valley, and they were very dry.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 3, 'Then He said to me, "Son of man, can these bones live?" I replied, "Lord God, [only] You know."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 4, 'He said to me, "Prophesy concerning these bones and say to them: Dry bones, hear the word of the LORD!');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 5, 'This is what the Lord God says to these bones: I will cause breath to enter you, and you will live.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 6, 'I will put tendons on you, make flesh grow on you, and cover you with skin. I will put breath in you so that you come to life. Then you will know that I am the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 7, 'So I prophesied as I had been commanded. While I was prophesying, there was a noise, a rattling sound, and the bones came together, bone to bone.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 8, 'As I looked, tendons appeared on them, flesh grew, and skin covered them, but there was no breath in them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 9, 'He said to me, "Prophesy to the breath, prophesy, son of man. Say to it: This is what the Lord God says: Breath, come from the four winds and breathe into these slain so that they may live!"');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 10, 'So I prophesied as He commanded me; the breath entered them, and they came to life and stood on their feet, a vast army.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 11, 'Then He said to me, "Son of man, these bones are the whole house of Israel. Look how they say: Our bones are dried up, and our hope has perished; we are cut off.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 12, 'Therefore, prophesy and say to them: This is what the Lord God says: I am going to open your graves and bring you up from them, My people, and lead you into the land of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 13, 'You will know that I am the LORD, My people, when I open your graves and bring you up from them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 14, 'I will put My Spirit in you, and you will live, and I will settle you in your own land. Then you will know that I am the LORD. I have spoken, and I will do [it]." [This is] the declaration of the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 15, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 16, '"Son of man, take a single stick and write on it: Belonging to Judah and the Israelites associated with him. Then take another stick and write on it: Belonging to Joseph-- the stick of Ephraim-- and all the house of Israel associated with him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 17, 'Then join them together into a single stick so that they become one in your hand.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 18, 'When your people ask you: Won''t you explain to us what you mean by these things?--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 19, 'tell them: This is what the Lord God says: I am going to take the stick of Joseph-- which is in the hand of Ephraim-- and the tribes of Israel associated with him, and put them together with the stick of Judah. I will make them into a single stick so that they become one in My hand.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 20, '"When the sticks you have written on are in your hand and in full view of the people,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 21, 'tell them: This is what the Lord God says: I am going to take the Israelites out of the nations where they have gone. I will gather them from all around and bring them into their own land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 22, 'I will make them one nation in the land, on the mountains of Israel, and one king will rule over all of them. They will no longer be two nations and will no longer be divided into two kingdoms.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 23, 'They will not defile themselves any more with their idols, their detestable things, and all their transgressions. I will save them from all their apostasies by which they sinned, and I will cleanse them. Then they will be My people, and I will be their God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 24, 'My servant David will be king over them, and there will be one shepherd for all of them. They will follow My ordinances, and keep My statutes and obey them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 25, '"They will live in the land that I gave to My servant Jacob, where your fathers lived. They will live in it forever with their children and grandchildren, and My servant David will be their prince forever.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 26, 'I will make a covenant of peace with them; it will be an everlasting covenant with them. I will establish and multiply them, and will set My sanctuary among them forever.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 27, 'My dwelling place will be with them; I will be their God, and they will be My people.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 37, 28, 'When My sanctuary is among them forever, the nations will know that I, the LORD, sanctify Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 1, 'The word of the LORD came to me:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 2, '"Son of man, turn your face toward Gog, of the land of Magog, the chief prince of Meshech and Tubal. Prophesy against him');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 3, 'and say: This is what the Lord God says: Look, I am against you, Gog, chief prince of Meshech and Tubal.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 4, 'I will turn you around, put hooks in your jaws, and bring you out with all your army, including horses and riders, who are all splendidly dressed, a huge company armed with shields and bucklers, all of them brandishing swords.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 5, 'Persia, Cush, and Put are with them, all of them with shields and helmets;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 6, 'Gomer with all its troops; and Beth-togarmah from the remotest parts of the north along with all its troops-- many peoples are with you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 7, '"Be prepared and get yourself ready, you and all your company who have been mobilized around you; you will be their guard.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 8, 'After a long time you will be summoned. In the last years you will enter a land that has been restored from war and regathered from many peoples to the mountains of Israel, which had long been a ruin. They were brought out from the peoples, and all of them [now] live securely.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 9, 'You, all of your troops, and many peoples with you will advance, coming like a thunderstorm; you will be like a cloud covering the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 10, '"This is what the Lord God says: On that day, thoughts will arise in your mind, and you will devise an evil plan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 11, 'You will say: I will go up against a land of open villages; I will come against a tranquil people who are living securely, all of them living without walls and without bars or gates--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 12, 'in order to seize spoil and carry off plunder, to turn your hand against ruins now inhabited and against a people gathered from the nations, who have been acquiring cattle and possessions and who live at the center of the world.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 13, 'Sheba and Dedan and the merchants of Tarshish with all its rulers will ask you: Have you come to seize spoil? Have you assembled your hordes to carry off plunder, to make off with silver and gold, to take cattle and possessions, to seize great spoil?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 14, '"Therefore prophesy, son of man, and say to Gog: This is what the Lord God says: On that day when My people Israel are dwelling securely, will you not know [this]');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 15, 'and come from your place in the remotest parts of the north-- you and many peoples with you, who are all riding horses-- a mighty horde, a huge army?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 16, 'You will advance against My people Israel like a cloud covering the land. It will happen in the last days, Gog, that I will bring you against My land so that the nations may know Me, when I show Myself holy through you in their sight.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 17, '"This is what the Lord God says: Are you the one I spoke about in former times through My servants, the prophets of Israel, who for years prophesied in those times that I would bring you against them?');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 18, 'Now on that day, the day when Gog comes against the land of Israel"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "My wrath will flare up.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 19, 'I swear in My zeal and fiery rage: On that day there will be a great earthquake in the land of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 20, 'The fish of the sea, the birds of the sky, the animals of the field, every creature that crawls on the ground, and every human being on the face of the earth will tremble before Me. The mountains will be thrown down, the cliffs will collapse, and every wall will fall to the ground.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 21, 'I will call for a sword against him on all My mountains"-- the declaration of the Lord God-- "and every man''s sword will be against his brother.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 22, 'I will execute judgment on him with plague and bloodshed. I will pour out torrential rain, hailstones, fire, and brimstone on him, as well as his troops and the many peoples who are with him.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 38, 23, 'I will display My greatness and holiness, and will reveal Myself in the sight of many nations. Then they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 1, '"As for you, son of man, prophesy against Gog and say: This is what the Lord God says: Look, I am against you, Gog, chief prince of Meshech and Tubal.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 2, 'I will turn you around, drive you on, and lead you up from the remotest parts of the north. I will bring you against the mountains of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 3, 'Then I will knock your bow from your left hand and make your arrows drop from your right hand.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 4, 'You, all your troops, and the peoples who are with you will fall on the mountains of Israel. I will give you as food to every kind of predatory bird and to the wild animals.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 5, 'You will fall on the open field, for I have spoken." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 6, '"I will send fire against Magog and those who live securely on the coasts and islands. Then they will know that I am the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 7, 'So I will make My holy name known among My people Israel and will no longer allow it to be profaned. Then the nations will know that I am the LORD, the Holy One in Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 8, 'Yes, it is coming, and it will happen." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God. "This is the day I have spoken about.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 9, '"Then the inhabitants of Israel''s cities will go out, kindle fires, and burn the weapons-- the bucklers and shields, the bows and arrows, the clubs and spears. For seven years they will use them to make fires.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 10, 'They will not gather wood from the countryside or cut [it] down from the forests, for they will use the weapons to make fires. They will take the loot from those who looted them and plunder those who plundered them." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 11, '"Now on that day I will give Gog a burial place there in Israel-- the Valley of the Travelers east of the Sea. It will block those who travel through, for Gog and all his hordes will be buried there. So [it] will be called the Valley of Hamon-gog.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 12, 'The house of Israel will spend seven months burying them in order to cleanse the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 13, 'All the people of the land will bury [them] and their fame will spread on the day I display My glory." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 14, '"They will appoint men on a full-time basis to pass through the land and bury the invaders who remain on the surface of the ground, in order to cleanse it. They will make [their] search at the end of the seven months.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 15, 'When they pass through the land and one of them sees a human bone, he will erect a marker next to it until the buriers have buried it in the Valley of Hamon-gog.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 16, 'There will even be a city named Hamonah [there]. So they will cleanse the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 17, '"Son of man, this is what the Lord God says: Tell every kind of bird and all the wild animals: Assemble and come! Gather from all around to My sacrificial feast that I am slaughtering for you, a great feast on the mountains of Israel; you will eat flesh and drink blood.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 18, 'You will eat the flesh of mighty men and drink the blood of the earth''s princes: rams, lambs, male goats, and bulls, all of them fatlings of Bashan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 19, 'You will eat fat until you are satisfied and drink blood until you are drunk, at My sacrificial feast that I have prepared for you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 20, 'At My table you will eat your fill of horses and riders, of mighty men and all the warriors." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 21, '"I will display My glory among the nations, and all the nations will see the judgment I have executed and the hand I have laid on them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 22, 'From that day forward the house of Israel will know that I am the LORD their God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 23, 'And the nations will know that the house of Israel went into exile on account of their iniquity, because they dealt unfaithfully with Me. Therefore, I hid My face from them and handed them over to their enemies, so that they all fell by the sword.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 24, 'I dealt with them according to their uncleanness and transgressions, and I hid My face from them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 25, '"So this is what the Lord God says: Now I will restore the fortunes of Jacob and have compassion on the whole house of Israel, and I will be jealous for My holy name.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 26, 'They will feel remorse for their disgrace and all the unfaithfulness they committed against Me, when they live securely in their land with no one to frighten [them].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 27, 'When I bring them back from the peoples and gather them from the countries of their enemies, I will demonstrate My holiness through them in the sight of many nations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 28, 'They will know that I am the LORD their God when I regather them to their own land after having exiled them among the nations. I will leave none of them behind.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 39, 29, 'I will no longer hide My face from them, for I will pour out My Spirit on the house of Israel." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 1, 'In the twenty-fifth year of our exile, at the beginning of the year, on the tenth day of the month in the fourteenth year after Jerusalem had been captured, on that very day the LORD''s hand was on me, and He brought me there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 2, 'In visions of God He took me to the land of Israel and set me down on a very high mountain. On its southern [slope] was a structure resembling a city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 3, 'He brought me there, and I saw a man whose appearance was like bronze, with a linen cord and a measuring rod in his hand. He was standing by the gate.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 4, 'He spoke to me: "Son of man, look with your eyes, listen with your ears, and pay attention to everything I am going to show you, for you have been brought here so that I might show [it] to you. Report everything you see to the house of Israel."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 5, 'Now there was a wall surrounding the outside of the temple. The measuring rod in the man''s hand was six units of 21 inches; each unit was the standard length plus three inches. He measured the thickness of the [wall] structure; it was about 10 feet, and its height was the same.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 6, 'Then he came to the gate that faced east and climbed its steps. He measured the threshold of the gate; it was 10 feet deep-- the first threshold was 10 feet deep.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 7, 'Each recess was about 10 feet long and 10 feet deep, and there was [a space of] eight and three-quarter feet between the recesses. The [inner] threshold of the gate on the temple side next to the gate''s portico was about 10 feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 8, 'Next he measured the portico of the gate;');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 9, 'it was 14 feet, and its pilasters were three and a half feet. The portico of the gate was on the temple side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 10, 'There were three recesses on each side of the east gate, each with the same measurements, and the pilasters on either side also had the same measurements.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 11, 'Then he measured the width of the gate''s entrance; it was 17 and a half feet, while the width of the gateway was 22 and three-quarter feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 12, 'There was a barrier of 21 inches in front of the recesses on both sides, and the recesses on each side were 10 and a half feet square.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 13, 'Then he measured the gateway from the roof of one recess to the roof of the [opposite] one; the distance was 43 and three-quarter feet. The openings of the recesses faced each other.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 14, 'Next, he measured the pilasters-- 105 feet. The gate extended around to the pilaster of the court.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 15, '[The distance] from the front of the gate at the entrance to the front of the gate''s portico on the inside was 87 and a half feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 16, 'The recesses and their pilasters had beveled windows all around the inside of the gateway. The porticos also had windows all around on the inside. Each pilaster was decorated with palm trees.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 17, 'Then he brought me into the outer court, and there were chambers and a paved surface laid out all around the court. Thirty chambers faced the pavement,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 18, 'which flanked the gates and corresponded to the length of the gates; [this] was the lower pavement.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 19, 'Then he measured the distance from the front of the lower gate to the exterior front of the inner court; it was 175 feet. [This] was the east; next the north [is described].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 20, 'He measured the gate of the outer court facing north, [both] its length and width.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 21, 'Its three recesses on each side, its pilasters, and its portico had the same measurements as the first gate: 87 and a half feet long and 43 and three-quarter feet wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 22, 'Its windows, portico, and palm trees had the same measurements as those of the gate that faced east. Seven steps led up to the gate, and its portico was ahead of them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 23, 'The inner court had a gate facing the north gate, like the one on the east. He measured the distance from gate to gate; it was 175 feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 24, 'He brought me to the south side, and there was also a gate on the south. He measured its pilasters and portico; they had the same measurements as the others.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 25, 'Both the gate and its portico had windows all around, like the other windows. It was 87 and a half feet long and 43 and three-quarter feet wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 26, 'Its stairway had seven steps, and its portico was ahead of them. It had palm trees on its pilasters, one on each side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 27, 'The inner court had a gate on the south. He measured from gate to gate on the south; it was 175 feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 28, 'Then he brought me to the inner court through the south gate. When he measured the south gate, it had the same measurements as the others.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 29, 'Its recesses, pilasters, and portico had the same measurements as the others. Both it and its portico had windows all around. It was 87 and a half feet long and 43 and three-quarter feet wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 30, '(There were porticoes all around, 43 and three-quarter feet long and eight and three-quarter feet wide.)');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 31, 'Its portico faced the outer court, and its pilasters were decorated with palm trees. Its stairway had eight steps.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 32, 'Then he brought me to the inner court on the east side. When he measured the gate, it had the same measurements as the others.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 33, 'Its recesses, pilasters, and portico had the same measurements as the others. Both it and its portico had windows all around. It was 87 and a half feet long and 43 and three-quarter feet wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 34, 'Its portico faced the outer court, and its pilasters were decorated with palm trees on each side. Its stairway had eight steps.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 35, 'Then he brought me to the north gate. When he measured [it], it had the same measurements as the others,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 36, '[as did] its recesses, pilasters, and portico. It also had windows all around. It was 87 and a half feet long and 43 and three-quarter feet wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 37, 'Its portico faced the outer court, and its pilasters were decorated with palm trees on each side. Its stairway had eight steps.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 38, 'There was a chamber whose door [opened] into the portico of the gate. The burnt offering was to be washed there.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 39, 'Inside the portico of the gate there were two tables on each side, on which to slaughter the burnt offering, sin offering, and restitution offering.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 40, 'Outside, as one approaches the entrance of the north gate, there were two tables on one side and two [more] tables on the other side of the gate''s portico.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 41, 'So there were four tables inside the gate and four outside, eight tables [in all] on which the slaughtering was to be done.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 42, 'There were also four tables of cut stone for the burnt offering, [each] 31 and a half inches long, 31 and a half inches wide, and 21 inches high. The utensils used to slaughter the burnt offerings and [other] sacrifices were placed on them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 43, 'There were three-inch hooks fastened all around the inside of the room, and the flesh of the offering was to be laid on the tables.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 44, 'Outside the inner gate, within the inner court, there were chambers for the singers: one beside the north gate, facing south, and another beside the south gate, facing north.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 45, 'Then the man said to me: "This chamber that faces south is for the priests who keep charge of the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 46, 'The chamber that faces north is for the priests who keep charge of the altar. These are the sons of Zadok, the ones from the sons of Levi who may approach the LORD to serve Him."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 47, 'Next he measured the court. It was square, 175 feet long and 175 feet wide. The altar was in front of the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 48, 'Then he brought me to the portico of the temple and measured the pilasters of the portico; they were eight and three-quarter feet [thick] on each side. The width of the gateway was 24 and a half feet, and the sidewalls of the gate were five and a quarter feet [wide] on each side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 40, 49, 'The portico was 35 feet across and 21 feet deep, and 10 steps led up to it. There were pillars by the pilasters, one on each side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 1, 'Next he brought me into the great hall and measured the pilasters; on each side the width of the pilaster was 10 and a half feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 2, 'The width of the entrance was 17 and a half feet, and the sidewalls of the entrance were eight and three-quarter feet [wide] on each side. He also measured the length of the great hall, 70 feet, and the width, 35 feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 3, 'He went inside [the next room] and measured the pilasters at the entrance; they were three and a half feet [wide]. The entrance was 10 and a half feet [wide], and the width of the entrance''s sidewalls on each side was 12 and a quarter feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 4, 'He then measured the length of the room adjacent to the great hall, 35 feet, and the width, 35 feet. And he said to me, "This is the most holy place."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 5, 'Then he measured the wall of the temple; it was 10 and a half feet [thick]. The width of the side rooms all around the temple was seven feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 6, 'The side rooms were arranged one above another in three stories of 30 rooms each. There were ledges on the wall of the temple all around to serve as supports for the side rooms, so that the supports would not be in the temple wall [itself].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 7, 'The side rooms surrounding [the temple] widened at each successive story, for the structure surrounding the temple [went up] by stages. This was the reason for the temple''s broadness as it rose. And so, one would go up from the lowest story to the highest by means of the middle one.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 8, 'I saw that the temple had a raised platform surrounding [it]; this foundation for the side rooms was 10 and a half feet high.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 9, 'The thickness of the outer wall of the side rooms was eight and three-quarter feet. The free space between the side rooms of the temple');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 10, 'and the [outer] chambers was 35 feet wide all around the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 11, 'The side rooms opened into the free space, one entrance toward the north and another to the south. The area of free space was eight and three-quarter feet wide all around.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 12, 'Now the building that faced the temple yard toward the west was 122 and a half feet wide. The wall of the building was eight and three-quarter feet thick on all sides, and the building''s length was 157 and a half feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 13, 'Then the man measured the temple; it was 175 feet long. In addition, the temple yard and the building, including its walls, were 175 feet long.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 14, 'The width of the front of the temple along with the temple yard to the east was 175 feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 15, 'Next he measured the length of the building facing the temple yard to the west, with its galleries on each side; it was 175 feet. The interior of the great hall and the porticoes of the court--');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 16, 'the thresholds, the beveled windows, and the balconies all around with their three levels opposite the threshold-- were overlaid with wood on all sides. [They were paneled] from the ground to the windows (but the windows were covered),');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 17, 'reaching to the top of the entrance, and as far as the inner temple and on the outside. On every wall all around, on the inside and outside, was a pattern');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 18, 'carved with cherubim and palm trees. There was a palm tree between each pair of cherubim. Each cherub had two faces:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 19, 'a human face turned toward the palm tree on one side, and a lion''s face turned toward it on the other. They were carved throughout the temple on all sides.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 20, 'Cherubim and palm trees were carved from the ground to the top of the entrance and on the wall of the great hall.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 21, 'The doorposts of the great hall were square, and the front of the sanctuary had the same appearance.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 22, 'The altar was made of wood, five and a quarter feet high and three and a half feet long. It had corners, and its length and sides were of wood. The man told me, "This is the table that stands before the LORD."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 23, 'The great hall and the sanctuary each had a double door,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 24, 'and each of the doors had two swinging panels. There were two panels for one door and two for the other.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 25, 'Cherubim and palm trees were carved on the doors of the great hall like those carved on the walls. There was a wooden canopyoutside, in front of the portico.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 41, 26, 'There were beveled windows and palm trees on both sides, on the sidewalls of the portico, the side rooms of the temple, and the canopies.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 1, 'Then the man led me out by way of the north gate into the outer court. He brought me to the group of chambers opposite the temple yard and opposite the building to the north.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 2, 'Along the length [of the chambers], which was 175 feet, there was an entrance on the north; the width was 87 and a half feet.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 3, 'Opposite the 35 [foot space] belonging to the inner court and opposite the paved surface belonging to the outer court, [the structure rose] gallery by gallery in three tiers.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 4, 'In front of the chambers was a walkway toward the inside, 17 and a half feet wide and 175 feet long, and their entrances were on the north.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 5, 'The upper chambers were narrower because the galleries took away more space from them than from the lower and middle stories of the building.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 6, 'For they were arranged in three stories and had no pillars like the pillars of the courts; therefore the upper chambers were set back from the ground more than the lower and middle stories.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 7, 'A wall on the outside ran in front of the chambers, parallel to them, toward the outer court; it was 87 and a half feet long.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 8, 'For the chambers on the outer court were 87 and a half feet long, while those facing the great hall were 175 feet [long].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 9, 'At the base of these chambers there was an entryway on the east side as one enters them from the outer court.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 10, 'In the thickness of the wall of the court toward the south, there were chambers facing the temple yard and the [western] building,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 11, 'with a passageway in front of them, just like the chambers that faced north. Their length and width, as well as all their exits, measurements, and entrances, were identical.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 12, 'The entrance at the beginning of the passageway, the way in front of the corresponding wall as one enters on the east side, was similar to the entrances of the chambers that were on the south side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 13, 'Then the man said to me, "The northern and southern chambers that face the temple yard are the holy chambers where the priests who approach the LORD will eat the most holy offerings. There they will deposit the most holy offerings-- the grain offerings, sin offerings, and restitution offerings-- for the place is holy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 14, 'Once the priests have entered, they must not go out from the holy area to the outer court until they have removed the clothes they minister in, for these are holy. They are to put on other clothes before they approach the public area."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 15, 'When he finished measuring inside the temple complex, he led me out by way of the gate that faced east and measured all around the complex.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 16, 'He measured the east side with a measuring rod; it was 875 feet by the measuring rod.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 17, 'He measured the north side; it was 875 feet by the measuring rod.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 18, 'He measured the south side; it was 875 feet by the measuring rod.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 19, 'Then he turned to the west side and measured 875 feet by the measuring rod.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 42, 20, 'He measured the temple complex on all four sides. It had a wall all around [it], 875 [feet] long and 875 [feet] wide, to separate the holy from the common.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 1, 'He led me to the gate, the one that faces east,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 2, 'and I saw the glory of the God of Israel coming from the east. His voice sounded like the roar of mighty waters, and the earth shone with His glory.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 3, 'The vision I saw was like the one I had seen when He came to destroy the city, and like the ones I had seen by the Chebar Canal. I fell facedown.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 4, 'The glory of the LORD entered the temple by way of the gate that faced east.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 5, 'Then the Spirit lifted me up and brought me to the inner court, and the glory of the LORD filled the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 6, 'While the man was standing beside me, I heard someone speaking to me from the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 7, 'He said to me: "Son of man, this is the place of My throne and the place for the soles of My feet, where I will dwell among the Israelites forever. [The house of] Israel and their kings will no longer defile My holy name by their [religious] prostitution and by the corpses of their kings at their high places.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 8, 'Whenever they placed their threshold next to My threshold and their doorposts beside My doorposts, with [only] a wall between Me and them, they were defiling My holy name by the abominations they committed. So I destroyed them in My anger.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 9, 'Now let them remove their prostitution and the corpses of their kings far from Me, and I will dwell among them forever.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 10, '"As for you, son of man, describe the temple to the house of Israel, so that they may be ashamed of their iniquities. Let them measure [its] pattern,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 11, 'and they will be ashamed of all that they have done. Reveal the design of the temple to them-- its layout with its exits and entrances-- its complete design along with all its statutes, design specifications, and laws. Write it down in their sight so that they may observe its complete design and all its statutes and may carry them out.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 12, 'This is the law of the temple: all its surrounding territory on top of the mountain will be especially holy. Yes, this is the law of the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 13, '"These are the measurements of the altar in units of length (each unit being the standard length plus three inches): the gutter is 21 inches [deep] and 21 inches wide, with a rim of nine inches around its edge. This is the base of the altar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 14, '[The distance] from the gutter on the ground to the lower ledge is three and a half feet, and the width [of the ledge] is 21 inches. There are seven feet from the small ledge to the large ledge, [whose] width is also 21 inches.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 15, 'The altar hearth is seven feet [high], and four horns project upward from the hearth.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 16, 'The hearth is square, 21 feet long by 21 feet wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 17, 'The ledge is 24 and a half feet long by 24 and a half feet wide, with four equal sides. The rim all around it is 10 and a half inches, and its gutter is 21 inches all around it. The altar''s steps face east."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 18, 'Then He said to me: "Son of man, this is what the Lord God says: These are the statutes for the altar on the day it is constructed, so that burnt offerings may be sacrificed on it and blood may be sprinkled on it:');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 19, 'You are to give a bull from the herd as a sin offering to the Levitical priests who are from the offspring of Zadok, who approach Me in order to serve Me." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 20, '"You must take some of its blood and apply [it] to the four horns of the altar, the four corners of the ledge, and all around the rim. In this way you will purify the altar and make atonement for it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 21, 'Then you must take away the bull for the sin offering, and it must be burned outside the sanctuary in the place appointed for the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 22, '"On the second day you are to present an unblemished male goat as a sin offering. They will purify the altar just as they did with the bull.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 23, 'When you have finished the purification, you are to present a young, unblemished bull and an unblemished ram from the flock.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 24, 'You must present them before the LORD; the priests will throw salt on them and sacrifice them as a burnt offering to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 25, 'You will offer a goat for a sin offering each day for seven days. A young bull and a ram from the flock, both unblemished, must also be offered.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 26, 'For seven days the priests are to make atonement for the altar and cleanse it. In this way they will consecrate it');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 43, 27, 'and complete the days [of purification]. Then on the eighth day and afterwards, the priests will offer your burnt offerings and fellowship offerings on the altar, and I will accept you." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 1, 'The man then brought me back toward the sanctuary''s outer gate that faced east, and it was closed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 2, 'The LORD said to me: "This gate will remain closed. It will not be opened, and no one will enter through it, because the LORD, the God of Israel, has entered through it. Therefore it will remain closed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 3, 'The prince himself will sit in the gateway to eat a meal before the LORD. He must enter by way of the portico of the gate and go out the same way."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 4, 'Then the man brought me by way of the north gate to the front of the temple. I looked, and the glory of the LORD filled His temple. And I fell facedown.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 5, 'The LORD said to me: "Son of man, pay attention; look with your eyes and listen with your ears to everything I tell you about all the statutes and laws of the LORD''s temple. Take careful note of the entrance of the temple along with all the exits of the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 6, '"Say to the rebellious people, the house of Israel: This is what the Lord God says: [I have had] enough of all your abominations, house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 7, 'When you brought in foreigners, uncircumcised in both heart and flesh, to occupy My sanctuary, you defiled My temple while you offered My food-- the fat and the blood. You broke My covenant with all your abominations.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 8, 'You have not kept charge of My holy things but have appointed [others] to keep charge of My sanctuary for you.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 9, '"This is what the Lord God says: No foreigner, uncircumcised in heart and flesh, may enter My sanctuary, not even a foreigner who is among the Israelites.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 10, 'Surely the Levites who wandered away from Me when Israel went astray, and who strayed from Me after their idols, will bear the consequences of their sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 11, 'Yet they will occupy My sanctuary, serving as guards at the temple gates and ministering at the temple. They will slaughter the burnt offerings and [other] sacrifices for the people and will stand before them to serve them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 12, 'Because they ministered to the house of Israel before their idols and became a sinful stumbling block to them, therefore I swore an oath against them"-- [this is] the declaration of the Lord God-- "that they would bear the consequences of their sin.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 13, 'They must not approach Me to serve Me as priests or come near any of My holy things or the most holy things. They will bear their disgrace and the consequences of the abominations they committed.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 14, 'Yet I will make them responsible for the duties of the temple-- for all its work and everything done in it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 15, '"But the Levitical priests descended from Zadok, who kept charge of My sanctuary when the Israelites went astray from Me, will approach Me to serve Me. They will stand before Me to offer Me fat and blood." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 16, '"They are the ones who may enter My sanctuary and draw near to My table to serve Me. They will keep My mandate.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 17, 'When they enter the gates of the inner court they must wear linen garments; they must not have on them anything made of wool when they minister at the gates of the inner court and within [it].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 18, 'They must wear linen turbans on their heads and linen undergarments around their waists. They are not to put on [anything that makes them] sweat.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 19, 'Before they go out to the outer court, to the people, they must take off the clothes they have been ministering in, leave them in the holy chambers, and dress in other clothes so that they do not transmit holiness to the people through their clothes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 20, '"They may not shave their heads or let their hair grow long, but must carefully trim their hair.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 21, 'No priest may drink wine before he enters the inner court.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 22, 'He is not to marry a widow or a divorced woman, but must marry a virgin from the offspring of the house of Israel, or a widow who is the widow of a priest.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 23, 'They must teach My people the difference between the holy and the common, and explain to them the difference between the clean and the unclean.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 24, '"In a dispute, they will officiate as judges and decide the case according to My ordinances. They must observe My laws and statutes regarding all My appointed festivals, and keep My Sabbaths holy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 25, 'A priest may not come [near] a dead person so that he becomes defiled. However, he may defile himself for a father, a mother, a son, a daughter, a brother, or an unmarried sister.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 26, 'After he is cleansed, he is to count off seven days for himself.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 27, 'On the day he goes into the sanctuary, into the inner court to minister in the sanctuary, he must present his sin offering." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 28, '"This will be their inheritance: I am their inheritance. You are to give them no possession in Israel: I am their possession.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 29, 'They will eat the grain offering, the sin offering, and the restitution offering. Everything in Israel that is permanently dedicated [to the LORD] will belong to them.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 30, 'The best of all the firstfruits of every kind and contribution of every kind from all your gifts will belong to the priests. You are to give your first batch of dough to the priest so that a blessing may rest on your homes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 44, 31, 'The priests may not eat any bird or animal that died naturally or was mauled by wild beasts.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 1, '"When you divide the land by lot as an inheritance, you must set aside a donation to the LORD, a holy portion of the land, eight and one-third [miles] long and six and two-thirds [miles] wide. This entire tract of land will be holy.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 2, 'In this area there will be a square [section] for the sanctuary, 875 by 875 [feet], with 87 and a half feet of open space all around it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 3, 'From this holy portion, you will measure off an area eight and one-third [miles] long and three and one-third [miles] wide, in which the sanctuary, the most holy place, will stand.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 4, 'It will be a holy area of the land to be used by the priests who minister in the sanctuary, who draw near to serve the LORD. It will be a place for their houses, as well as a holy area for the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 5, 'There will be [another area] eight and one-third [miles] long and three and one-third [miles] wide for the Levites who minister in the temple; it will be their possession for towns to live in.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 6, '"As the property of the city, you must set aside an area one and two-thirds [of a mile] wide and eight and one-third [miles] long, adjacent to the holy donation [of land]. It will be for the whole house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 7, 'And the prince will have the area on each side of the holy donation [of land] and the city''s property, adjacent to the holy donation and the city''s property, stretching to the west on the west side and to the east on the east side. [Its] length will correspond to one of the [tribal] portions from the western boundary to the eastern boundary.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 8, 'This will be his land as a possession in Israel. My princes will no longer oppress My people but give the [rest of the] land to the house of Israel according to their tribes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 9, '"This is what the Lord God says: You have gone too far, princes of Israel! Put away violence and oppression and do what is just and right. Put an end to your evictions of My people." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 10, '"You must have honest balances, an honest dry measure, and an honest liquid measure.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 11, 'The dry measure and the liquid measure will be uniform, with the liquid measure containing five and a half gallons and the dry measure [holding] half a bushel. Their measurement will be one-tenth of the standard larger capacity measure.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 12, 'The shekel will weigh 20 gerahs. Your mina will equal 60 shekels.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 13, '"This is the contribution you are to offer: Three quarts from five bushels of wheat and three quarts from five bushels of barley.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 14, 'The quota of oil in liquid measures will be one percent of every cor. [The cor equals] 10 liquid measures [or] one standard larger capacity measure, since 10 liquid measures equal one standard larger capacity measure.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 15, 'And [the quota] from the flock is one animal out of every 200 from the well-watered pastures of Israel. [These are] for the grain offerings, burnt offerings, and fellowship offerings, to make atonement for the people." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 16, '"All the people of the land must take part in this contribution for the prince in Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 17, 'Then the burnt offerings, grain offerings, and drink offerings for the festivals, New Moons, and Sabbaths-- for all the appointed times of the house of Israel-- will be the prince''s responsibility. He will provide the sin offerings, grain offerings, burnt offerings, and fellowship offerings to make atonement on behalf of the house of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 18, '"This is what the Lord God says: In the first [month], on the first [day] of the month, you are to take a young, unblemished bull and purify the sanctuary.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 19, 'The priest must take some of the blood from the sin offering and apply [it] to the temple doorposts, the four corners of the altar''s ledge, and the doorposts of the gate to the inner court.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 20, 'You must do the same thing on the seventh [day] of the month for everyone who sins unintentionally or through ignorance. In this way you will make atonement for the temple.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 21, '"In the first [month], on the fourteenth day of the month, you are to celebrate the Passover, a festival of seven days [during which] unleavened bread will be eaten.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 22, 'On that day the prince will provide a bull as a sin offering on behalf of himself and all the people of the land.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 23, 'During the seven days of the festival, he will provide seven bulls and seven rams without blemish as a burnt offering to the LORD on each of the seven days, along with a male goat each day for a sin offering.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 24, 'He will also provide a grain offering of half a bushel per bull and half a bushel per ram, along with a gallon of oil for every half bushel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 45, 25, 'At the festival [that begins] on the fifteenth day of the seventh month, he will provide the same things for seven days-- the same sin offerings, burnt offerings, grain offerings, and oil.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 1, '"This is what the Lord God says: The gate of the inner court that faces east must be closed during the six days of work, but it will be opened on the Sabbath day and opened on the day of the New Moon.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 2, 'The prince should enter from the outside by way of the gate''s portico and stand at the doorpost of the gate while the priests sacrifice his burnt offerings and fellowship offerings. He will bow in worship at the threshold of the gate and then depart, but the gate must not be closed until evening.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 3, 'The people of the land will also bow in worship before the LORD at the entrance of that gate on the Sabbaths and New Moons.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 4, '"The burnt offering that the prince presents to the LORD on the Sabbath day is to be six unblemished lambs and an unblemished ram.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 5, 'The grain offering will be half a bushel with the ram, and the grain offering with the lambs will be whatever he wants to give, as well as a gallon of oil for every half bushel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 6, 'On the day of the New Moon, [the burnt offering] is to be a young, unblemished bull, as well as six lambs and a ram without blemish.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 7, 'He will provide a grain offering of half a bushel with the bull, half a bushel with the ram, and whatever he can afford with the lambs, together with a gallon of oil for every half bushel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 8, 'When the prince enters, he must go in by way of the gate''s portico and go out the same way.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 9, '"When the people of the land come before the LORD at the appointed times, whoever enters by way of the north gate to worship must go out by way of the south gate, and whoever enters by way of the south gate must go out by way of the north gate. No one must return through the gate by which he entered, but must go out by the opposite gate.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 10, 'When the people enter, the prince will enter with them, and when they leave, he will leave.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 11, 'At the festivals and appointed times, the grain offering will be half a bushel with the bull, half a bushel with the ram, and whatever he wants to give with the lambs, along with a gallon of oil for every half bushel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 12, '"When the prince makes a freewill offering, whether a burnt offering or a fellowship offering as a freewill offering to the LORD, the gate that faces east must be opened for him. He is to offer his burnt offering or fellowship offering just as he does on the Sabbath day. Then he will go out, and the gate must be closed after he leaves.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 13, '"You must offer an unblemished year-old male lamb as a daily burnt offering to the LORD; you will offer it every morning.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 14, 'You must also prepare a grain offering every morning along with it: three quarts, with one-third of a gallon of oil to moisten the fine flour-- a grain offering to the LORD. [This is] a permanent statute [to be observed] regularly.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 15, 'They will offer the lamb, the grain offering, and the oil every morning as a regular burnt offering.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 16, '"This is what the Lord God says: If the prince gives a gift to each of his sons as their inheritance, it will belong to his sons. It will become their property by inheritance.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 17, 'But if he gives a gift from his inheritance to one of his servants, it will belong to that servant until the year of freedom, when it will revert to the prince. His inheritance belongs only to his sons; it is theirs.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 18, 'The prince must not take any of the people''s inheritance, evicting them from their property. He is to provide an inheritance for his sons from his own property, so that none of My people will be displaced from his own property."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 19, 'Then he brought me through the entrance that was at the side of the gate, into the priests'' holy chambers, which faced north. I saw a place there at the far western end.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 20, 'He said to me, "This is the place where the priests will boil the restitution offering and the sin offering, and where they will bake the grain offering, so that they do not bring [them] into the outer court and transmit holiness to the people."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 21, 'Next he brought me into the outer court and led me past its four corners. There was a [separate] court in each of its corners.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 22, 'In the four corners of the [outer] court there were enclosed courts, 70 [feet] long by 52 and a half [feet] wide. All four corner areas had the same dimensions.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 23, 'There was a [stone] wall around the inside of them, around the four of them, with ovens built at the base of the walls on all sides.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 46, 24, 'He said to me: "These are the kitchens where those who minister at the temple will cook the people''s sacrifices."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 1, 'Then he brought me back to the entrance of the temple and there was water flowing from under the threshold of the temple toward the east, for the temple faced east. The water was coming down from under the south side [of the threshold] of the temple, south of the altar.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 2, 'Next he brought me out by way of the north gate and led me around the outside to the outer gate that faced east; there the water was trickling from the south side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 3, 'As the man went out east with a measuring line in his hand, he measured off a third of a mile and led me through the water. It came up to [my] ankles.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 4, 'Then he measured off a third [of a mile] and led me through the water. It came up to [my] knees. He measured off another third [of a mile] and led me through [the water]. It came up to [my] waist.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 5, 'Again he measured off a third of a [mile], and it was a river that I could not cross [on foot]. For the water had risen; it was deep enough to swim in, a river that could not be crossed [on foot].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 6, 'He asked me, "Do you see [this], son of man?" Then he led me back to the bank of the river.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 7, 'When I had returned, I saw a very large number of trees along both sides of the riverbank.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 8, 'He said to me, "This water flows out to the eastern region and goes down to the Arabah. When it enters the sea, the sea of foul water, the water [of the sea] becomes fresh.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 9, 'Every [kind of] living creature that swarms will live wherever the river flows, and there will be a huge number of fish because this water goes there. Since the water will become fresh, there will be life everywhere the river goes.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 10, 'Fishermen will stand beside it from En-gedi to En-eglaim. These will become places where nets are spread out to dry. Their fish will consist of many different kinds, like the fish of the Mediterranean Sea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 11, 'Yet its swamps and marshes will not be healed; they will be left for salt.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 12, 'All [kinds of] trees providing food will grow along both banks of the river. Their leaves will not wither, and their fruit will not fail. Each month they will bear fresh fruit because the water [comes] from the sanctuary. Their fruit will be used for food and their leaves for medicine."');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 13, 'This is what the Lord God says: "This is the border you will [use to] divide the land as an inheritance for the 12 tribes of Israel. Joseph will receive two shares.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 14, 'You will inherit it in equal portions, since I swore to give it to your ancestors. So this land will fall to you as an inheritance.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 15, '"This is to be the border of the land: On the north side it will extend from the Mediterranean Sea by way of Hethlon and Lebo-hamath to Zedad,');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 16, 'Berothah, and Sibraim (which is between the border of Damascus and the border of Hamath), [as far as] Hazer-hatticon, which is on the border of Hauran.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 17, 'So the border will run from the sea to Hazar-enon at the border of Damascus, with the territory of Hamath to the north. This will be the northern side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 18, 'On the east side it will run between Hauran and Damascus, along the Jordan between Gilead and the land of Israel; you will measure from the [northern] border to the eastern sea. This will be the eastern side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 19, 'On the south side it will run from Tamar to the waters of Meribath-kadesh, and on to the Brook [of Egypt] as far as the Mediterranean Sea. This will be the southern side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 20, 'On the west side the Mediterranean Sea will be the border, from the [southern] border up to a point opposite Lebo-hamath. This will be the western side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 21, '"You are to divide this land among yourselves according to the tribes of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 22, 'You will allot it as an inheritance for yourselves and for the foreigners living among you, who have fathered children among you. You will treat them like native-born Israelites; along with you, they will be allotted an inheritance among the tribes of Israel.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 47, 23, 'In whatever tribe the foreigner lives, you will assign his inheritance there." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 1, '"Now these are the names of the tribes: From the northern end, along the road of Hethlon, to Lebo-hamath as far as Hazar-enon, at the northern border of Damascus, alongside Hamath and extending from the eastern side to the sea, will be Dan-- one portion.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 2, 'Next to the territory of Dan, from the east side to the west, will be Asher-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 3, 'Next to the territory of Asher, from the east side to the west, will be Naphtali-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 4, 'Next to the territory of Naphtali, from the east side to the west, will be Manasseh-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 5, 'Next to the territory of Manasseh, from the east side to the west, will be Ephraim-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 6, 'Next to the territory of Ephraim, from the east side to the west, will be Reuben-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 7, 'Next to the territory of Reuben, from the east side to the west, will be Judah-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 8, '"Next to the territory of Judah, from the east side to the west, will be the portion you donate [to the LORD], eight and one-third [miles] wide, and as long as one of the [tribal] portions from the east side to the west. The sanctuary will be in the middle of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 9, '"The [special] portion you donate to the LORD will be eight and one-third [miles] long and three and one-third [miles] wide.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 10, 'This holy donation will be set apart for the priests [alone]. It will be eight and one-third [miles long] on the northern side, three and one-third [miles] wide on the western side, three and one-third [miles] wide on the eastern side, and eight and one-third [miles] long on the southern side. The LORD''s sanctuary will be in the middle of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 11, 'It is for the consecrated priests, the sons of Zadok, who kept My charge and did not go astray as the Levites did when the Israelites went astray.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 12, 'It will be a special donation for them out of the [holy] donation of the land, a most holy place adjacent to the territory of the Levites.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 13, '"Next to the territory of the priests, the Levites [will have an area] eight and one-third [miles] long and three and one-third [miles] wide. The total length will be eight and one-third [miles] and the width three and one-third [miles].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 14, 'They must not sell or exchange any of it, and they must not transfer this choice [part] of the land, for it is holy to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 15, '"The remaining [area], one and two-thirds [of a mile] wide and eight and one-third [miles long], will be for common use by the city, for [both] residential and open space. The city will be in the middle of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 16, 'These are the city''s measurements: one and a half [miles] on the north side; one and a half [miles] on the south side; one and a half [miles] on the east side; and one and a half [miles] on the west side.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 17, 'The city''s open space will extend: 425 [feet] to the north, 425 [feet] to the south, 425 [feet] to the east, and 425 [feet] to the west.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 18, '"The remainder of the length alongside the holy donation will be three and one-third [miles] to the east and three and one-third [miles] to the west. It will run alongside the holy donation. Its produce will be food for the workers of the city.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 19, 'The city''s workers from all the tribes of Israel will cultivate it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 20, 'The entire donation will be eight and one-third [miles] by eight and one-third [miles]; you are to set apart the holy donation along with the city property as a square [area].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 21, '"The remaining [area] on both sides of the holy donation and the city property will belong to the prince. He will own [the land] adjacent to the [tribal] portions, next to the eight and one-third [miles] of the donation as far as the eastern border and next to the eight and one-third [miles of the donation] as far as the western border. The holy donation and the sanctuary of the temple will be in the middle of it.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 22, 'Except for the Levitical property and the city property in the middle of the area belonging to the prince, the area between the territory of Judah and that of Benjamin will belong to the prince.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 23, '"As for the rest of the tribes: From the east side to the west, will be Benjamin-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 24, 'Next to the territory of Benjamin, from the east side to the west, will be Simeon-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 25, 'Next to the territory of Simeon, from the east side to the west, will be Issachar-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 26, 'Next to the territory of Issachar, from the east side to the west, will be Zebulun-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 27, 'Next to the territory of Zebulun, from the east side to the west, will be Gad-- one [portion].');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 28, 'Next to the territory of Gad toward the south side, the border will run from Tamar to the waters of Meribath-kadesh, to the Brook [of Egypt], and out to the Mediterranean Sea.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 29, 'This is the land you are to allot as an inheritance to Israel''s tribes, and these will be their portions." [This is] the declaration of the Lord God.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 30, '"These are the exits of the city: On the north side, which measures one and a half [miles],');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 31, 'there will be three gates facing north, the gates of the city being named for the tribes of Israel: one, the gate of Reuben; one, the gate of Judah; and one, the gate of Levi.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 32, 'On the east side, which is one and a half [miles], there will be three gates: one, the gate of Joseph; one, the gate of Benjamin; and one, the gate of Dan.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 33, 'On the south side, which measures one and a half [miles], there will be three gates: one, the gate of Simeon; one, the gate of Issachar; and one, the gate of Zebulun.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 34, 'On the west side, which is one and a half [miles], there will be three gates: one, the gate of Gad; one, the gate of Asher; and one, the gate of Naphtali.');
INSERT INTO BIBLE VALUES 
('Ezekiel', 48, 35, 'The perimeter [of the city] will be six [miles], and the name of the city from that day on will be: Yahweh Is There."');
